title: wassail
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Keep warm in crock-pot or on stove.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Best served with corn chips.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion. Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into three thinner biscuits.
Lay each layer over a greased mini muffin pan cup.
Using your fingers or mini tart shaper to press each biscuit layer into cup.
Fill cups with bacon mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 30 cups.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender; cool. Alternate layers of carrots, onion and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate at least one day before serving.

title: peanut butter bonbons(serves 60)
directions: Melt together peanut butter and butter; add sugar and Rice Krispies.
Mix together and form into balls.
Melt Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip bonbons in chocolate mix using 2 forks.
Place on waxed paper.
Makes about 125.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, then form it into balls. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well and then add corn and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add chopped prunes.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool frost with Fake Whip Cream Frosting.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler on low.
In large heavy kettle, put sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil just to melt sugar.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter. Stir.
Then add rice cereal.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press in pan with damp hands.
Frost with chip mixture.
Cut before it sets.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock pot and mix together well. Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Cook for 1 hour in crock-pot.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients; beat well.
Pour in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
(If dough seems dry, work with hands.)
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen appetizers.

title: irish oatmeal bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl the flour, oats, baking powder and salt. In a medium bowl, mix egg, honey and milk and beat well.
Pour egg mixture into oat mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon just until dry ingredients are moist.
Will not be smooth.
Spread in pan. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn out while still warm and brush top with butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube chicken or turkey.
Layer Fritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the chicken, soups, pimentos and chilies.
Spread items on Fritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
When ready to serve, top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and black olives.

title: sour cream jello mold
directions: Prepare Jell-O and add to pineapple and strawberries.
Pour half into mold until it hardens.
Spread sour cream over Jell-O. Add rest of Jell-O mixture.
Harden until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Melt together sugar and corn syrup, but do not boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate and butterscotch morsels and spread on top of Rice Krispies.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain all fruit well. Arrange half of the fruit in greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Crumble 6 cookies on top. Repeat the layer. Slice butter on top and pour Amaretto over the fruit. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix all ingredients, then add ice. Stir well.
Serves approximately 35.

title: crumbly top apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together. Add to the apple slices. Arrange apples in pie shell.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onions until tender; drain.
Mix with sour cream and soup.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch greased pan or baking dish. Top with dry dressing dotted with margarine, then layer zucchini mixture with more dressing mix on top.
Crushed cornflake crumbs may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
In another bowl, toss apples with cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Spread 1/3 of batter in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover with half the apples.
Repeat layers.
Spoon remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.
Just before serving, dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: aunt betty's cheese ball
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together cheese, onion, horseradish and Miracle Whip.
Cut beef into small slivers and put 1/4 of it into mixture.
Set rest of beef aside.
Mix cheese mixture into a ball.
Place remaining beef on ball sides.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove when cool.
Chill.
Top with fruit topping, preserves, nuts or chocolate (be creative).

title: almond fudge topped shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Mix in flour. With floured hands, press into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly until chips are melted.
Stir in almond extract.
Spread evenly over shortbread.
Sprinkle with almonds; press down firmly.
Chill 3 hours.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: elaine's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Then add flour and milk a little at a time, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water.
Dissolve and add other ingredients. Mix and refrigerate.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Mash figs up real good; mix with other ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook from 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 pints of preserves.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and core green tomatoes.
Slice crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in flour with salt and pepper.
Fry slowly in butter until soft.
Turn and fry other side; drain on paper towels.

title: no-fat snack
directions: Place shake mix in Ziploc bag.
Add washed grapes (still damp).
Shake well to coat each grape.
Freeze.
Enjoy as a candy substitute.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tarragon in sour cream
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Dip both sides of chicken in margarine; place skin side up in pan. Sprinkle with salt, tarragon and pepper.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Form into small balls. Place on pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Mix cocoa into sugar; then sift 3 or 4 times.
Melt the butter. Then cut the cheese into chunks (so it will melt faster).
Then put the cheese into the butter and return to the microwave until the cheese is melted.
Lightly butter a large mold (we use a large turkey platter).
With rubber gloves on, butter your hands to mix the candy.
With the sugar and cocoa in a large mixing bowl, pour the hot butter and cheese in the center of sugar.
Mix with spoon or hands until you can't see any sugar.
Then mix in the nuts. Spread on the mold.
Let cool at room temperature or put in the refrigerator 2 hours, then cut desired size.
Can keep in the freezer.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Mix together cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted oleo.
Pat crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl combine cream cheese with chilled milk.
Beat with mixer until fluffy, gradually adding 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour mixture into crumb crust. Top with a few additional crumbs. Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken in bouillon cubes or canned chicken broth.
Grate Monterey Jack cheese.
Dip tortillas in broth to soften, then add chicken, chopped onion and broth to each tortilla.
Roll up and put in baking dish, seam side down.

title: triple chocolate rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a Bundt pan. (You may grease pan with your choice of shortening, oil or spray.)

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar together.
Put milk over double boiler.
Add flour mixture and egg yolks.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add butter, flavoring and coconut.
Pour into pie shell (graham cracker or baked shell).
Beat egg whites and extra sugar.
Pour onto pie.

title: cream of broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft. Stir in flour and next 4 ingredients; cook over low heat until flour is smooth. Allow flour to cook until light golden brown; remove from heat and slowly add milk and chicken broth. Mix well. Return to heat and cook over low heat until thickened to medium thickness. Add cheese; stir until melted. Add chopped broccoli and let soup cook on lowest heat for 15 to 30 minutes or until flavors blend. Serves 8 to 12.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Cut unpeeled cucumbers in thin slices.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Barely cover cucumber slices with mixture of 1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve undrained or drain and serve with French dressing or mayonnaise. Arrange on greens with tomato slices.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend and beat 4 minutes. Bake in 325° oven. Cool 45 minutes.

title: noreen's favorite walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, corn syrup, eggs, flour, butter and vanilla until blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange walnuts on top. Bake in lower third of oven for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until brown; drain off fat.
Add salt and Worcestershire sauce.
In casserole dish, add 1/2 of cabbage. Cover with ground beef mixture.
Repeat layers; cover with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with stuffing.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips and cheese together. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: famous chicken muenster
directions: Cut chicken breast (raw) into bite-size pieces. Roll chicken pieces in flour and pepper mixture. Lightly brown chicken in 1 stick melted butter and garlic clove. Shred cheese. Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Pour on mushrooms and liquid, covering the chicken. Sprinkle with the cheese. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon yogurt coffee cake
directions: Combine
flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, sugar and oatmeal; set aside.
In another bowl combine honey, eggs, yogurt, margarine, grated lemon peel and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients;
mix.
Pour
into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30
minutes.
Or
make
muffins and bake approximately 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil chopped potatoes until they are soft.
Combine mayonnaise, relish, pimentos and chopped eggs.
Begin mixing.
Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Ready to eat or can be refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: nutty honey drumsticks
directions: Arrange chicken on foiled baking sheet.
Melt butter; stir in honey and mustard and simmer, stirring for 5 minutes.
Brush honey mixture generously on chicken.
Combine crumbs and pecans and sprinkle over chicken. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together; blend well.
Pour over the Rice Chex in a large bowl.
Stir to coat.
Put the powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Pour cooled Rice Chex into bag; shake well.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Grease 2-inch muffin pans. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes or until golden. Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon together in a bowl.
Dip tops in melted butter or margarine, then the sugar-cinnamon mix.
Makes 24 (2-inch) muffins.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook 8 minutes on 400°.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add whipped topping.
Mix Jell-O and water together. Add strawberries.

title: mock champagne
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir well until sugar dissolves.
Store in freezer overnight or longer.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in pan; boil for 1 minute.
Take off stove. Add remaining ingredients quickly.
Drop on wax paper.

title: jambalaya
directions: Simmer chicken parts, celery tops, dried onion, bay leaf, garlic and water until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from bone and set aside.
Strain and skim fat from broth.
Then saute in nonstick pan or in 1 teaspoon oil your ham, onion, garlic, green pepper and celery.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomato puree, chicken broth, mushrooms, thyme, chili powder, cayenne pepper and rice and simmer 20 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer until rice is done and liquid is absorbed (about 30 minutes).
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked bean winter soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sausage, in soup pot.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add sausage, simmer another 30 minutes.
Even better if made a day before and reheated.

title: garden-topped red snapper
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix pesto, lemon juice, carrot and leek. Cut margarine into small pieces.
Place in rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Place fish on margarine.
Spread vegetable mixture over fish.
Cover and bake 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Cover and cook meat and mash with potato masher; add all other ingredients that need cooking.
When tender, add tomatoes and juice the last 30 minutes.
Good with bread or crackers.

title: lemon goodies
directions: Combine the butter, powdered sugar and flour and pat into a 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat together eggs, sugar, flour, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour over hot crust and bake again at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: fruit treats
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in a bowl until stiff.
Spread on pie and bake until lightly brown.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine (melted).
Whip with beater Dream Whip, milk, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Put 1/2 cracker crumbs in dish, pressing down to make crust (or base).
Add 1/2 Dream Whip mixture.
Add pie filling, other 1/2 of Dream Whip mixture.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Chill before serving.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash in halves and remove seeds.
Place 1 teaspoon butter in each half; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and onion powder (to taste).
May also cube squash, if desired.
Place in pan; cover with tinfoil.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: chicken special
directions: Cover chicken in water, adding soda.
Soak overnight.
Drain. Combine beaten egg with lemon juice, vinegar and milk.
Cover chicken and soak overnight; drain.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo until soft.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Butter bottom of jelly roll pan and put into pan.
Ummmmm Ummmmm good.

title: red hot salad
directions: Melt red hots in water over low heat stirring to prevent sticking.
When red hots are melted, dissolve Jell-O.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour in a mold and chill.
Recipe can
easily be doubled.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown chops; drain. In greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, then chops.
Add Lipton onion mushroom recipe soup mix thoroughly blended with water.
Bake covered 1 hour or until potatoes and chops are tender.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift first three ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mix.
Add nuts. Roll into logs in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator or freezer.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: punch for 50
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes; let cool.
Add juices. Put bananas in blender and add this together.
Freeze.
Before serving, add ginger ale.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place cinnamon and sugar into a plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces a few at a time.
Shake to coat well.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Put in a salad bowl all the fruit, sliced very thin.
Add onion (red), sliced very, very thin.
Drain pineapple.
Pour creamy onion dressing.
Mix well.
Make sure all fruit is fresh, except pineapple.

title: brown bread
directions: One cup of Sweet Milk,

title: chicken stew with dumplings
directions: Saute bacon in large pan until crisp.
Saute chicken pieces until light brown.
Add carrots, onion, celery, 1 3/4 cup water, chicken broth, rosemary and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover, simmer 20 minutes.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup water. Stir into stew mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring until thickened. Remove bay leaf.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix biscuit mix and milk.
Drop by tablespoon into stew.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes, cover, cook 10 minutes more.

title: poke salad stems(1900 or older)
directions: Put oil in frying pan.
Get hot.
Take poke stems, sliced like okra, and roll in flour and meal.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook until tender.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients; add flour mixture with applesauce.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls about the size of a big marble and fry.
Drain off fat.
Mix 3/4 cup of ketchup and 1 cup of water; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice, raisins and sugar.
Also, add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: roasted vegetable pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place leeks in a shallow roasting pan and drizzle with olive oil and chicken broth.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix honey, powdered milk and peanut butter in a large bowl. Add granola and mix again.
Form into balls as small or large as you want.
Chill or freeze for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix all ingredients together and bake approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: michigan rocks cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as they come.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop cookies on sheet and bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Blend flour and butter in skillet.
Add broth; cook until thickens.
Stir in salt.
Layer broccoli, 1/2 of sauce and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread remaining mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Broil until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peppermint ice cream dessert
directions: Mix the crackers, nuts and melted butter together and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat pudding with milk.
Fold in ice cream.
Freeze.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush peppermint candy and spread on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate zucchini finely and drain. Combine in a large bowl the eggs, oil and sugars.
Sift together and add gradually to egg mixture 2 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then add to egg and flour mixture the grated, drained zucchini, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour the loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot chicken salad #1
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese.
Place in a large rectangular dish.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. (I prefer to refrigerate in a bowl, then transfer to a dish the next day.)
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coca cola cake icing
directions: In a sauce pan combine butter, cocoa and coke.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over sifted powdered sugar and beat well.
Add nuts and spread over cake.

title: red hot pickles
directions: Heat until red hots are melted.
Pour over sliced cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Next morning, heat to boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: turtle nut cake
directions: Prepare mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set remaining butter aside.
Bake batter in the pan for 18 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: funnel cake
directions: Heat oil in frying pan until very hot.
Drop mixture in pan from a funnel and fry until golden brown; turn and fry other side. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly; put into bowl.
Pour other ingredients on top of cucumbers; stir well.
Put cucumbers into freezer bags and freeze.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles; let them cool.
Brown ground beef, then add to spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 11-inch pan, layer 3 layers of noodles, meat, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Top off with a thick layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together broccoli, rice and Cheez Whiz in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add onion and celery. Cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
May top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: big batch meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, broth, bread crumbs, onion and pepper.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into meatballs and place on broiler pan or other roasting rack.
Brush tops with soy sauce and bake about 12 minutes at 375°.
Turn if needed.
Cool and freeze in portions needed.
Great to use for spaghetti, soups or sweet and sour meatballs.

title: au gratin potatoes for the gang(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Combine salt, butter, pepper, onion, soup, milk and sour cream; stir in potatoes.
Turn half of the mixture into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Top with remaining potato mixture and the remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced (but not peeled) squash and onion together in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes after the water boils.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots, then fold in zucchini mixture.

title: pete's 5-alarm chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
In a stew pot, saute peppers, onion, garlic and jalapenos 5 minutes.
Add meat, tomatoes, beans and bay leaf.
Stir thoroughly.
Add chili powder to taste. Simmer on low heat, covered, for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally. Can be served with grated Cheddar cheese and a hard roll.

title: barbecued lamb, sonoma style(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, wine, chiles, garlic, Italian seasoning and mustard.
Mix well.
Place lamb in shallow dish and pour mixture over it.
Turn to coat top side.
Cover and marinate overnight, turning again once.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt margarine; mix with graham crackers.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add cream cheese and sugar; beat until smooth.

title: chess brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and then pat out onto an 8 x 11-inch glass pan.
Beat eggs; add cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mix in glass pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes to 1 hour, depending on oven.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In plastic bag, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and bouillon. Marinate 4 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken and broil or grill as desired.
Place on tortillas.
Top with cheese, tomatoes, onions and lettuce.
Fold.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: cathy's microwave meatloaf
directions: *Spices are to taste.

title: mashed potato cookies
directions: Mix these ingredients together well.
Add 1 (6 ounce) package chocolate chips and stir.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: mom's company hash browns
directions: Spread potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; drizzle melted butter on potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, pepper and garlic together.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain fat. Add cream of chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Ranch Style beans. Mix and let simmer for 20 minutes. Add shredded cheese and simmer for 10 minutes. Serve over Fritos.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: parmesan cheese dip
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator one day.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.

title: lentil and brown rice soup(great low-fat recipe)
directions: Heat lentils, rice, water, cumin, salt, pepper and dry soup mix to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until lentils are tender, about 40 minutes.
Stir in spinach, parsley and lemon juice.
Cook until spinach is wilted. Serve with lemon slices if desired.

title: walnut cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together in large bowl for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Use an angel food pan that the bottom comes out.
Do not grease pan.
Leave in pan for 1 hour to cool.
Loosen edges and remove.
Can be sliced thin as nut bread or cut slices in quarters as cookies.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well. Add raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
Freezes well.

title: chicken dinner casserole
directions: Cook onion with broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Mix together next 7 ingredients.
Add broccoli and onion and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice while hot.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Spray baking dish with oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop all vegetables small and cook for 1 hour or until thick. Need to be cooked in a heavy pot or it will stick when it starts getting thick.
Place in jars and seal.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust; cool.
Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup. Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops of red food coloring; cool.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Spread on bottom of cooled pie shell.
Fill shell with remaining berries over top.
Chill at least 3 hours or until set.

title: dutch hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
To the 3 tablespoons of drippings, add celery, onion, salt and flour; cook 5 minutes.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper and water; bring to a boil and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour, layer by layer, over potatoes in casserole.
Add crumbled bacon on top.
Bake for 30 minutes with lid on at 350°.

title: irish bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes in a greased pan, 10 minutes at 375° and the rest at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill for at least 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: low cholesterol macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions, omitting oil and salt; drain.
Rinse macaroni under cold running water and drain again.
Set macaroni aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and oleo thoroughly.
Beat egg, then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until light and fluffy. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes or until light brown around edges.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Blend the meal, salt, sugar, butter, water and 1 cup milk in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add 1 cup milk and eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve piping hot with lots of butter.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put unopened milk in a saucepan.
Cover completely with water and boil for 3 hours.
Keep can covered with water.
After 3 hours, let can cool.
Open can and pour into bowl and stir.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Very good if frozen or very well chilled.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper; flour the shrimp.
Fry the bacon; remove from the pan.
Stir-fry the onion; remove from the pan.
Add the floured shrimp to the bacon grease; cook over medium heat until pinkish.
Add about 1 cup of water; stir to thicken. Crumble in bacon; add the onion.
May need more water if too thick.
Serve over rice or grits.
Delicious.
Serves several, depending on appetite.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly. Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Mix thoroughly after each addition. Add nuts; mix and pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until done. I put the soda into the buttermilk and dredge the nuts in flour before adding to mixture.

title: kentucky gingerbread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Combine molasses and hot water and add alternately with flour mixture. Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then remove from pan and cut in squares.

title: roast lamb with noodles
directions: Put lamb in shallow dish or pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add butter.
Brown in moderate oven.
Turn pieces from time to time.
Add tomatoes and 1 pint of water.
Bake until meat is tender, stirring frequently.
When meat is very tender, remove from pan and keep meat hot.
Add remaining stock to pan.
Season to taste and bring to boil.
Add macaroni and cook until tender and has absorbed liquid.
Arrange hot meat on a platter and smother with macaroni.
Or return meat to noodles and garnish with cheese.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add shrimp, water chestnuts, bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Remove from heat. Beat eggs until well mixed.
Pour over vegetable and shrimp mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat, without stirring, for about 20 minutes, until eggs are done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Set aside.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles with points to the center of pizza pan. Press bottom and sides to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on low rack of oven.
Crust will be fluffy.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle on cheeses.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients. Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Press rolls into bottom of pan.
Brown sausage and sprinkle over rolls.
Add cheese.
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings together.
Pour over cheese layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple smiles
directions: Cut apples into slices.
Dip the apple slices into the lemon juice.
(This keeps the apple from turning brown.)
Pat the apple dry and spread peanut butter on one side of the apple slice.

Place marshmallows on the peanut butter on the apple, close to the skin, then place another apple slice with peanut butter toward the marshmallow on the other slice, making sure that the skin is on the same side as the other slice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet for crust.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Mix together Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Hidden Valley salad mix; spread on crust.
Top with raw vegetables. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: broccoli-tomato salad
directions: Chop broccoli and green onions including the tops.
Quarter the tomatoes.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and lemon pepper and stir into vegetables.

title: old ham
directions: Ideally, an old ham weighs 16 to 20 pounds.
Trim well and scrub clean.
Soak overnight in cold water to cover.
Put ham in fresh water; bring to boil and pour this water off.
Repeat if ham is very old and salty.
With fat side up, bring slowly to boiling and simmer for an hour or more.
Then add the sugar, spices (except whole cloves) and vinegar.
Pour all over ham.
Turn ham fat side down and simmer about an hour.
Turn it over again and cook until the skin blisters or it is tender.
This will take an additional 4 or 5 hours, depending on size of ham.
Let stand overnight in the water in which the
ham was cooked.
Skin, then sprinkle with bread crumbs, a little brown sugar and paprika and brown in the oven.
Remove from the oven; score and stick with whole cloves.
Cool thoroughly before slicing thin.

title: blondies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325 for 30-35 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Must start with cold oven; do not preheat.

title: chicken chili
directions: With fork, beat egg and milk.
In bowl mix together flour, seasoning mix and Accent.
Dip chicken in egg; then in flour mixture.
Heat corn oil in fry pan over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Reduce heat. Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Drain.
Serve hot or cold.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together Bisquick, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken in mixture and bake at 425° for 45 minutes, turn chicken and bake 15 minutes longer or until done.
Tastes like fried chicken.

title: hawaiian dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, onions and seasonings together. Slice chipped beef and mix in with other ingredients.
Hollow out bread and put dip in bread.
Save the rest of the bread and serve on the side.
Serve with bread and crackers.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Melt Velveeta and stir until smooth. Combine all ingredients and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often or place in crock-pot on low heat.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix by hand.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Serve warm.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats- let stand. Cream sugars and shortening. Beat eggs into mixture. sift dry ingredients and add to shortening mixture. Add oats, beat well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased, floured 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Mix together rice, soups, milk and dry soup in bowl.
In large baking dish, with cover, place chicken breasts in bottom (spray with Pam).
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake, covered, 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Check after 2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine in a large bowl with butter. Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Place in
a buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef
and	drain;	pour
beef in casserole dish. Layer rest	of ingredients as listed.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: killer brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup Pet milk in top of double boiler. Mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup Pet milk and butter.
Bake half of cake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour melted caramels on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Add 1/3 cup Pet milk to remaining cake mix.
Spread over chocolate chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Don't overbake. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef
and
onion
over
medium heat until beef is brown. Drain. Stir
in
seasoning
mix.
Spread
in plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in
blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake
until knife inserted into center and edge comes out
clean
to 10 minutes longer).
Cool 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: In baking dish, put roast, covered with onion soup mix and mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° or 325° for 3 hours or boil roast. When tender, add onion soup mix and soup and bake in oven.

title: oven meal
directions: Place ingredients in baking dish in order given: potatoes, celery, hamburger, green peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Yields 6 servings.
Put lid on it.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter slowly together.
Add alternately evaporated milk and powdered sugar, stirring constantly over medium heat until it starts to bubble.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: your other chili
directions: In a small skillet over medium heat, toast cumin seed, oregano, basil and Mrs. Dash shaking pan occasionally until fragrant, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil very hot.
Add onion, peppers, carrots, garlic, toasted herbs, paprika, cayenne and chili powder.
Saute 10 to 15 minutes. Add canned tomato and some tomato juice and jalapeno peppers. Bring to a boil.
Add beans.
Continue to simmer.
Add fresh tomatoes.
Heat.
Top with yogurt.
Makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: You will need 4 (12-inch) squares aluminum foil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-angel food cream cake
directions: Empty pineapple into heavy saucepan.
Add vanilla pudding mix and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until very thick. Remove from heat; cool and chill well.
Meanwhile, split cake into 3 layers.
Whip 1 pint cream and fold into pineapple mixture.
Add chopped cherries.
Spread generously between layers, sides and top of cake.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes 10 servings.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar; add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water and fruit juice.
Chill.
Spoon sherbet into punch; add ginger ale.
Yields about 6 1/2 quarts.

title: onion chicken
directions: Lightly fry chicken in oil. Prepare baking sheet by covering with foil. Put French fried onions in a Ziploc bag and crush with rolling pin or cooking mallet. Pour into bowl or dish. Melt the butter, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and garlic powder in saucepan. Dip the fried chicken in butter mixture and then coat with the crushed fried onions. Place chicken pieces on foil-covered baking sheet. Spoon remaining French fried onions onto chicken pieces and drizzle with leftover butter mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with bread cubes.
Fry sausage and drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over bread and sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine milk, slightly beaten eggs and seasonings. Pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Very good for breakfast or brunch.

title: complete hamburger casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix beef, onion, salt and pepper in ungreased 2-quart casserole. Arrange vegetables on meat; pour cheese soup on vegetables.
Cover with frozen potato rounds. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until potatoes are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy bottomed 2-quart saucepan over high heat, stir sugar, corn syrup and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 300° (hard crack stage), about 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts, margarine, vanilla and baking soda. Quickly spread in thin layer on greased baking sheet; cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container for up to 2 weeks.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Cook hamburg and stir until it has lost pink color.
Stir in onion and garlic and cook until onion is transparent.
Add flour, seasonings and mushrooms and cook five minutes.
Stir in the soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add the sour cream and heat through.
Can sprinkle parsley on top.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peggy's famous otter creek cakes(pinto bean cake)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add creamed mixture.
Stir in beans, apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apple delights(servings:  4)
directions: Mix together in order given.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the sweet potatoes, orange juice and pineapple.
Add enough orange juice to keep from being stiff.
Melt butter; add. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Cover the top with marshmallows.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, until marshmallows are brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter.
Spread thinned cream cheese on bread to edge of each slice.
Cut each slice into 3 equal strips and roll up.
Tuck ends together.
Dip rolled bread strips in melted butter; roll in sugar mixture.
Place on wax paper and freeze.
After removing from freezer, bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let sit before serving to cook and firm. Delicious!

title: yiddish pudding
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease two 9-inch pie pans and line with
greased
wax	paper.	Pour
into
pans and bake 40 minutes in a 300° oven.
Let cool in the pans.
Beat whipping cream
and spread
over
layers
like icing a cake.
Sprinkle crushed peanuts over layers of icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for 6 minutes according to package.
Drain and put into cake pan.
Cook hamburg, mushrooms, onion and pepperoni in a fry pan.
Drain and put into the cake pan.
Mix well with the macaroni.
Spread the cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: three-day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 2 layers.
When layers are cool, split in half.
While cake is cooling, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Reserve 1 cup of sour cream mixture.
Spread remainder between the layers. Blend whipped topping and reserved sour cream mixture.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before eating.

title: garfish nuggets
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut fish in small pieces and season with salt and pepper.
Soak fish in mixture for about 2 hours, roll in flour and deep fry (always use flour, not cornmeal.)

title: pizza #2
directions: Make the crust.
First put sauce on.
Toppings next.
Put in oven.
Bake for 100 minutes at 250 degrees.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken, let cool and then bone chicken.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, add chicken and cooked rice.
Mix in both cans of soup.
Add mushrooms to mixture.
Season to taste.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Casserole should not be overdry, but not too moist.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut off stems and scoop out mushrooms; mince, reserving caps. Saute minced bacon in skillet until crisp. Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Add butter to bacon and bacon fat. Saute minced shallots and garlic until soft. Add minced mushrooms and saute until liquid is almost absorbed.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs and thoroughly mix.
Blend in milk. Salt and pepper to taste. Fill mushroom caps with mixture and top each with bacon square to cover. Use all of the mixture.
Mushrooms will be heaped very high.
Broil until bacon is crisp and browned.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in thin wafer slices.
Slice onion this thin and separate into rings.
Mix together the mushroom soup and sour cream.
In casserole dish, layer pork chops, onion and potato mixture and soup mixture.
Salt and pepper each layer to taste. Bake at 375° about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Crisp Crumbs:
Combine 1 cup flour, rolled oats, brown sugar and butter; mix with a pastry cutter or fork to get the crumb texture just right.
Set aside while you prepare the apples and spices.

title: tostada platter
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Set aside and keep warm.
In saucepan, combine undrained green beans and kidney beans; heat and drain.
Heat tortillas in microwave or oven.

title: cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves and cut off bottom of cauliflower.
Set flat in bowl.
Put 2 tablespoons water on bottom.
Cover.
Microwave 8 minutes on High.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray nonstick baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Using fork, stir in buttermilk until just combined.
Sprinkle reserved 2 teaspoons flour on work surface; roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Using 3-inch round biscuit cutter, cut out 12 biscuits, gathering up scraps and re-rolling dough as necessary.
Place biscuits on prepared baking sheet; bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down french toast
directions: Melt butter in 8 to 9-inch square pan as oven preheats to 400°.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the top of melted margarine. Place pineapple over brown sugar evenly.
Beat eggs, milk and salt until blended.
Soak bread in egg mix until soft.
Arrange bread on top of pineapple.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven until light brown.
Invert entire pan onto large serving platter or with pancake turner lift each serving off onto plate.

title: beet jelly
directions: In a saucepan, add beet juice, lemon juice, and Sure Jell and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and raspberry Jello.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes stirring continually.
Skim and pour into hot dry jars.
Makes 4 to 5 pt.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased casserole dish, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl combine nuts, dates and cherries.
In another bowl stir flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add to nut mixture, stirring until nuts and fruit are well coated.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nut mixture.
Mix well; pour in greased and wax paper-lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine. Pour in sugar and flour.
Cream good, then add egg yolks and beat good.
Add milk and coconut. Stir good and pour in pie shell.
Cook on bottom rack at 375° until done.

title: chocolate frostee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in ice cream can and freeze until hard.
(Yummy good.)

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve juice).
Add water to juice to fill cup and heat to boiling.
Add to Jello and dissolve thoroughly. Let cool (not in refrigerator).
Gently stir in 7 to 8 oz. ginger ale.
Mix pineapple and cranberry sauce together well and fold into Jello.
Set in refrigerator until lightly set.
Mix package of Dream Whip according to directions on box.
Soften cream cheese until soft and spreadable.
Spread over Jello mixture.

title: quick guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with Fritos.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into cakes.
Fry in small amount of oil until brown on both sides.

title: chocolate pie (baked in the shell)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour, cocoa and melted margarine. Mix real well.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into 2 prepared pie shells and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn down to 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until middle is set.
Add meringue and brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add green beans and vinegar and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: busy day chicken divan
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, spread broccoli and top with chicken. Separately, mix soup with next 3 ingredients, and pour over the chicken. Sprinkle the cheese over soup and top with crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. GREAT MEAL IN ONE DISH!!

title: mexican layer casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart glass bowl.
Add onion. Microwave (High), uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is set; stir once.
Stir to break meat into small pieces; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, sauce mix and water.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir once. Place chips in 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish; crush slightly. Spoon hot meat mixture evenly onto chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with lettuce and tomato.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Cook and stir onion in reserved fat.
Add Velveeta process cheese spread and milk; stir until Velveeta process cheese spread is melted.
Crumble bacon.
Add bacon, beans and pepper to skillet.
Mix lightly. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces; this should take about 2 months.
Season well with salt, pepper and oregano.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook four weeks at 465°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook until tender.
Drain well and combine with sour cream, chicken soup, carrot, onion and 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Mix remaining half with butter for topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pig pickin' dh
directions: Add the oil and juice from the oranges to the cake mix.
Add the eggs; beat 4 minutes on high speed.
Fold in the oranges. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add the instant vanilla pudding and the crushed pineapple to the Cool Whip.
Spread between layers and on top.
May use three 9-inch layers or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: no bake club cracker bars
directions: Boil for 7 minutes (stirring all the time).
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with crackers (Club).
Use 1/2 of filling and put over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and put other half of filling on that.
Then frost with layer of chocolate frosting.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until tender and set aside.
Mix flour or cornstarch with sugar and salt.
Separate eggs and set whites aside.
Beat yolks with fork and mix with milk.
Mix with cornstarch and sugar mixture and cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil while stirring for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Sweeten rice to taste and mix with pudding.
Whip egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar until foamy.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on while whipping, until swirls are thick.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour pudding and rice mixture in baking dish and spread with meringue.
Brown in preheated oven at 350°.

title: oyster pie
directions: Layer oysters, crackers and butter. Make 2 layers. Beat egg; add milk, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: *Well drained cottage cheese may be substituted for Ricotta.

title: rum balls
directions: Crush wafers fine (I put in processor).
Mix all ingredients well; roll into balls size of walnut.
Put on a tray to dry.
Can be rolled in powdered sugar.

title: hot cha-cha
directions: Brown meat along with seasoning package.
If you do not have a seasoning package, just add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and salt to taste.

To prepare each individual plate, just start by placing amount of Fritos in center of dish, then spoon on some of the meat mixture, warmed beans, then chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, onion, cheese and hot sauce.
You could also add avocado dip or black olives, if desired.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto batter.
Cut through batter several times to give it the marble effect. Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips, if desired.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine margarine and cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this for topping.
Pat crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme and spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: fried pickles
directions: Coat pickles with onion ring mix and fry in very hot oil. Delicious.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well creamed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add unsifted flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed sugar and butter mixture. Use some flour to dredge orange slices, dates, nuts and coconut. Fold in dates, nuts, etc.
If baked in a large pan bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 300°.
Smaller loaf pan less baking time.
Line pans with foil, then grease and flour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar and stir.
Add buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheesy macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese.
Mix other ingredients together and then mix them all together.

title: lo-fat cheesecake
directions: Spray spring-form pan bottom and 2-inches on sides with Pam. Sprinkle with graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar; pat down. Drain cottage cheese several times.
Transfer to food processor with cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, sour cream, eggs, egg whites and flour.
Process until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Crush walnuts; mix with mini-chocolate chips and sprinkle on cake.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn off and leave in oven for 1/2 hour.
Cool completely.

title: easy no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, cocoa, butter and cream.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls of about 1 teaspoon mixture.
Store in a closed container, wrapping in waxed paper or putting it between layers.

title: turkey divan
directions: Place broccoli in a shallow 2-quart dish.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave on High 11 to 12 minutes. Separate spears; drain and return to dish.
Set aside.
Place soup in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until very hot.
Stir in turkey; cover and microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Spoon sauce over broccoli and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 minute.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, soda and egg white. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan for 35 to 38 minutes at 350 degrees. During the last 10 minutes of baking, heat the condensed milk and caramel in a saucepan on medium heat until well mixed. As soon as the cake is done, remove from oven and poke holes in the top and immediately pour the hot caramel sauce over the top and sprinkle with 1/2 of Heath bites. After it is completely cooled cut into squares and top with Cool Whip and the rest of the Heath bites. Keep in refrigerator.

title: sister helen's never fail frosting
directions: Boil the sugar, milk and margarine or butter for 1 minute, then add the chocolate chips and vanilla.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed and Jell-O begins to thicken.
Add drained pineapple and mashed bananas.
Divide mixture in half.
Pour half mixture in 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish to congeal in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter. Stir in flour. Add milk.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat. Stir in corn, eggs and seasonings.
Pour into greased, shallow dish. Sprinkle with corn flakes (or bread crumbs) which has been mixed with melted butter.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super beans pot
directions: Fry onions and garlic in fat until soft.
Mix other ingredients in and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: butterfingers
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water to hard crack.
Stir twice.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and spread on buttered cookie sheet. Spread shredded chocolate on top.
Let melt and spread. Cool and cut.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Crush graham crackers to make fine crumbs.
Mix crumbs with brown sugar and chopped walnuts.
Set aside.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Arrange in buttered 8-inch baking dish in alternate layers with crumb mixture.
Dot top with butter and pour lemon juice and water over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 350° for about 30 minutes until apples are cooked to a jelly. Serve hot or cold with cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Add vanilla and melted white chocolate to cream cheese mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square baking pan or dish.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Yields 2 pounds.

title: vegi-dip
directions: Mix with blender until smooth.
Can be used for raw vegetables or on salads and baked potatoes.

title: french coffee cake rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water, let stand 10 to 14 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar and salt; cut oleo in like pie crust.
Add warm milk and beaten egg yolks.
Stir until soft dough is formed, then add yeast and water.
Pur in refrigerator overnight.

title: cherry holiday cake
directions: Bring raisins to boil, drain and cool.
Mix together butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, then add cherries, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into ungreased tube pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350° and then lower to 300°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans, greased. Put chocolate chips on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 1 1/2 hours before removing from pans.

title: smokey links and cheese on buns
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients all together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread on the English muffins, open-faced.
Place under broiler until brown for about 5 minutes.

title: fried rabbit
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and paprika.
Use to coat rabbit pieces.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook rabbit, a few pieces at a time, until browned on all sides, removing pieces to platter as they brown.
When all browned, return to skillet and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until rabbit is fork-tender.

title: annie's surprise cake
directions: Beat all together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix in a mixer and form into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in crushed English walnuts just before serving. (I use one 2.5 ounce package dried beef.)

title: crepes(hungarian palacinta)
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Combine flour and salt.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter (set aside skillet); beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Heat buttered skillet over medium low heat. For each crepe, pour a scant 2 tablespoons batter in the skillet. Immediately rotate pan.
Cook until light brown; turn and brown other side.
Stack between sheets of waxed paper or paper toweling until ready to use.

title: armenian rice
directions: Brown butter and rice, add bouillon, salt and pepper and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Watch that rice doesn't become too dry.

title: grandma lively's potato salad
directions: Soak mustard seed and celery seed in vinegar overnight. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
May add extra mayonnaise prior to serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast prune cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream the butter, honey, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine oats, flour, bran, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually mix into butter mixture.
Stir in prunes and walnuts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Stir together all but onion rings.
Let stand overnight in casserole.
In morning, add onion rings (crumble on top).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab melts
directions: Cut English muffins into quarters.
Spread with crab mixture and freeze for 30 minutes. Broil until puffy and bubbly.

title: linda's baked salmon potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes; scoop out potatoes and mix with the oleo, salt, pepper, onion flakes, milk and salmon.
Put in potato skins. Bake at 350° until hot.
Sprinkle tops with cheese.

title: company potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place in a bowl or other container in the following layers: first, lettuce; then green bell pepper, frozen peas, mayonnaise, sliced boiled eggs, cheese and last sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix ingredients until crumbled.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook all ingredients to hard crack stage (except for cinnamon oil).
Remove from heat; add cinnamon oil.
Pour onto oiled pan. Crack into pieces when hard.

title: scotch-a-rows
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup just to a boil.
Take off and add peanut butter.
Mix well and add Rice Krispies.
Butter pan (9 x 13-inch) and pour up.
Just melt (do not cook) 6 ounces chocolate chips and 6 ounces butterscotch chips and pour over top.
Let set and cut in squares.

title: carol's favorite cake
directions: Use a yellow cake mix and bake as directed.
While cake bakes, in a saucepan over medium-high heat, mix pineapple with juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves completely and mixture reaches a boil.
As soon as cake is done, remove from oven and punch holes all over (use a toothpick so holes will go through cake).
Spoon hot pineapple mixture over cake.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Remove from heat.
Cool until lukewarm and stir in vanilla.
Pour over cake and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, spread with Cool Whip and garnish with coconut.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix altogether until well blended. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
While hot, cover with marshmallows. Have icing ready.
Cover while hot.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, mustard and pepper.
Lay crescent rolls out on greased cookie sheet.
Layer sausage, hash browns and cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over all and let settle. Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Stir 1 teaspoon soda into applesauce and add to first ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend into batter.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Mix together with Bisquick, gradually.
Set in refrigerator until cold.
Form into small balls and bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until brown. Makes about 70.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shape into small balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pineapple marshmallow salad
directions: Reserve juice from pineapple.
Combine flour and sugar, then add egg and juice.
Heat until thick.
Pour over pineapple in casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: speedy 24-hour salad
directions: Prepare instant pudding according to package directions.
Fold in whipping cream.
Drain liquids from fruits; cut up cherries. Fold well drained fruits into pudding mixture along with marshmallows and bananas.
Chill overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: holiday ham loaf(kathlyn claudia dumont oswalt hollopeter, kettering, ohio)
directions: Combine ingredients in order, mixing thoroughly.
Pack ham loaf firmly into a greased 9 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Pour off juices, loosen edges and invert onto platter.
After pouring off juice, cool at least 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: unbaked cookies(like candy)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil hard.
Pour over oatmeal mixed with cocoa.
Add vanilla.
Stir together quickly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chopped nuts may be added if you desire.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook the noodles in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes and drain. Chop garlic and parsley together. Place the oil in a skillet; heat and add mushrooms, bay leaf, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Cook slowly for 4 minutes; stir. Place the butter in another saucepan; melt and add the flour. Blend. Add hot chicken broth, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Remove from the heat. Add cream and wine; stir well. Place drained noodles in a buttered oven casserole. Spoon mushroom mixture over the noodles and arrange chicken over mushrooms. Pour the cream sauce over all and sprinkle the cheese on top. Bake in preheated moderate 350° oven for about 15 minutes. Serve with a green salad, a ripe pear, a slice of Fontina cheese and a glass of dry Orvieto. Serves 4.

title: oven-fried zucchini sticks
directions: Trim zucchini and cut into sticks, about the size of French fries.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat egg with water.
Roll each zucchini stick in egg mixture and then in the crumbs.
Place coated zucchini sticks on a baking sheet and spoon butter over them.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven at 400° until tender and lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 26 sticks.
Serves 4.

title: crepes
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add milk and shortening.
Sift flour with salt and sugar; add to egg mixture.
With hand beater, beat until smooth.
On griddle or in chafing dish, heat salad oil or shortening.
Drop crepe batter in 5 rounds on griddle; cook, turning once, until a light brown on both sides.

title: rosemary walnuts
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan. Remove from heat and add seasonings. Add the walnuts and toss gently, but well. Place the walnuts in a shallow roasting pan in one layer. Bake at 325° until richly brown (about 10 to 15 minutes), shaking occasionally. Nicest when served warm.

title: dessert bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and 1 stick melted margarine together.
Pat out in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: forget-em-cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until foamy; add salt.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating mixture until soft peaks form.
Fold vanilla, chocolate morsels and pecans into beaten egg whites.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Combine sugar, spices and apple juice.
Add cranberries and chopped apple.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave 9 to 11 minutes on High until skin of berries split and juice is slightly thickened.
Stir in walnuts.
Cool before serving.

title: honey raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside. In a large bowl, stir together cereal, milk and honey.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes until soft.
Add egg and oil. Beat well. Add flour mixture, stirring to combine.
Pour into 12 muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk and corn.
Mix again.
Pour into a casserole baking dish, about 2-inches deep and pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: grandma barb's homemade noodles
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, salt and milk.
Add enough flour to a make a stiff dough. Roll out very thin on floured board.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Slice in thin strips about 1/8-inch thick (a pizza cutter works great for this).
Spread out and let dry for about 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 3 cups of noodles.

title: gold coast banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare yellow cake mix as directed, except stir baking soda into mixture before adding liquid and eggs.
Use 1/4 cup less water and add 1 cup mashed bananas.
Fold 1/2 cup chopped nuts into batter.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a medium size bowl mix all ingredients.
Microwave just long enough to melt cheese.
Stir and serve with chips of your choice.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients until smooth with electric mixer. Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour half of batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven.
Drizzle glaze over cake and cool.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: apricot date squares
directions: Blend together margarine and sugar. Cream until light and fluffy. Mix remaining ingredients together and combine with margarine-sugar mixture. Put a little more than half of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Press firmly into place.

title: pita chips
directions: Cut pita bread into wedges.
Separate each wedge into 2 pieces.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with lemon juice. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash or other salt-free herb mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until crisp.

title: scramble snack(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix all ingredients in very large roaster.
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 2 hours, stirring and turning mixture with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.
Be careful not to crush cereals.
Makes about 8 quarts.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Soak beef overnight in a mixture of any barbecue sauce, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook the next day in the liquids at least 3 hours at 350°.
Meat is done when tender.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Beat soft butter at high speed until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Gradually beat in sugar until fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and nuts until blended.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers together to spread on top of Veg-All and corn as topping.
Bake.

title: low-fat lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix and sugar; add oil and next 4 ingredients.
Mix at medium speed for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour batter into Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; drizzle with Lemon Glaze and cool completely on wire rack; 156 calories, 2.8 protein, 4.7 fat, .2 cholesterol, 168 mg. sodium.

title: hamburg special(good quick meal to make)
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ruby goulden's tomato aspic salad
directions: Heat soup and add lemon jello.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon in frying pan until brown.
Remove and leave enough drippings to cover bottom of pan.
Chop onion and bell pepper and brown in drippings.
Next, add tomatoes.
Stir in salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar and sugar; stir.
Crumble bacon over top. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes on medium.
Serve over rice.

title: turkey neck soup
directions: Cover cleaned necks with water.
Cook until well done.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Very good with cornbread.

title: chocolate raisin nut clusters
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole place chocolate, peanuts and raisins.
Cover.
Microwave on Low 4 to 5 minutes, or until chocolate is melted.
Stir mixture until chocolate covers peanuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Chill until firm. Makes about 24 pieces.

title: almond butter toffee
directions: Cook on high; stir with wooden spoon only to soft crack.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into regular size cookie sheet.
Pour chocolate chips on top; spread when melted.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter and milk. Beat until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Top with cool.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix well the liquid ingredients; stir into dry ingredients. Cook on hot griddle that is slightly greased.
Reduce heat.
When pancake begins to bubble, turn and brown on other side.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit juices and add enough water to equal 2 3/4 cups liquid.
Mix with pudding and cook to boiling.
Cool and add to fruit.
Add bananas last.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with maraschino cherries if desired.

title: fudge icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add butter, dash of salt and Pet milk in a pan.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken bavarian
directions: Mix rice, soup and water.
Add curry and parsley.
Place in greased casserole.
Lay chicken on top.
Seal tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cook rice and mix in soy sauce together.
Cook chicken, onions and celery until done.
Mix in bean sprouts, chestnuts, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and cooked rice.
Simmer until done, 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Sift in dry ingredients, then stir in apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cut and drain pimentos. Drain pineapple and use juice as part of water in making jello. Make jello according to package directions. Let jello congeal to a soft consistency, stir in cream cheese, mayonnaise, pimentos, nuts celery and pineapple. Put in refrigerator, let congeal to a firm consistency. Serve with or without lettuce.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix lightly and roll onto a floured board or foil.
Cut by cutter and place in greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Combine ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: taco rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Drain olives and chilies and add to mixture.
Mix in Cheddar cheese, salt and onions.
Spread mixture onto tortillas and roll up.
Place in refrigerator and chill.
Remove and cut into 1/2-inch rolls.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly.
Add oil, slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat for a few minutes. Store in refrigerator but not near freezing unit.
This dressing will never separate but stir each time before use.
This is good on fruit or green salad.

title: blueberry peach trifle
directions: In large bowl, combine milk, water and lemon rind; mix well. Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into a 4-quart glass bowl.
Top with half the cake cubes, the peaches, half the remaining pudding mixture, the remaining cake cubes, then the blueberries and remaining pudding spread to 1 inch of edge of bowl.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
