title: soup for a group
directions: Brown bones or knuckles in oven.
In a large kettle, boil 2 quarts water; add knuckles, salt, pepper, onion and celery leaves. Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Strain the stock.
Brown the stew meat in bottom of kettle.
Cover with water and let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Clean and chop vegetables.
Add stock to stew meat, then add all other ingredients.
Cook until done.
Can add 1 box frozen lima beans or mixed vegetables, if desired.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Crush crackers and add lemon pepper seasoning.
Roll chicken in cracker mixture.
Put in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: kristin's mint bars
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use package directions, adding an extra egg.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour with dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour milk to first mixture. Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 375 ° for about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind the cranberries. Add the marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight. Add the diced apples, grapes, nuts and salt. Whip the cream and fold it in. This should keep about 4 days.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Dust roast with salt, pepper and flour.
Braise all sides of roast in hot stew pot (1 to 2 tablespoons of oil may be added). Add in all the other ingredients, except carrots and noodles. Simmer for at least 3 hours.
Add carrots 1 hour before completion.
Serve over cooked noodles.
(Slow cookers are great; let it cook all day!)

title: dump cake
directions: Put the pineapple into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (use glass if possible).
Put pie filling over pineapple and crumble (dry) cake mix over pie filling.
Spread nuts and slice butter over nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. (I like to melt the butter first and then spread it over the cake mix.)
Ovens may vary.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool.

title: coconut creme cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg whites.
Beat for 2 minutes at highest speed of mixer.
Reduce speed to low; beat for 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in top of cake with a toothpick. Pour cream of coconut over cake while still warm and spread whipped topping over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut and cover. Chill at least 4 hours.
Cut cake into squares to serve.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine corn syrup, water, salt and sugar in a 3-quart saucepan.
Boil to 265° (hard ball stage).
Beat egg whites stiff in large mixer bowl; gradually beat in the boiling syrup.
Beat until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat again and pour into a pan, greased slightly with salad oil or butter.
(I have a favorite pan that measures 7 x 11-inches).
Cut into squares when cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice, cream cheese, milk and flavoring. Pour into 2 pie crusts. Cover with glaze. Top with cool whip and garnish with berries.

title: mini strawberry milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend at low speed until the ice is dissolved.
Makes 1 serving.
Contains 137 calories.
This is filling and satisfying.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and pecans and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into crusts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cook rice and drain well.
Melt butter in skillet and add onion, soup and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Place in oven at 350° until lightly browned on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla and mix.
Add all dry ingredients (sifted together). Add zucchini and mix well.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: Cook everything but egg whites in double boiler until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a baked crust and top with meringue of egg whites.

title: vegetable dish broccoli supreme
directions: Place broccoli on paper towel and drain.
Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add carrots and onion and saute 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in broccoli, croutons and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with spray.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sauteed asparagus
directions: Wash, peel and cut asparagus.
Heat oil in pan.
When oil is hot, turn heat down to medium and stir-fry asparagus.
Add salt, sugar and liquid and steam for 4 minutes.
Uncover; turn up heat and cook, stirring to evaporate liquid.
Stir in butter; season. Serves 4.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt together first 4 ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Pour in hash browns; put salt and pepper on.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Cover and let stand for 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put any amount of eggs in a pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Let eggs boil for 15 minutes.
Take off of heat and cool under cold water.
Peel eggs while warm.
While eggs are boiling, go ahead and mix all other ingredients in a large pot on the stove. Heat mixture and taste.
For sweeter eggs use more sugar.
For sour eggs use more vinegar.
Put warm eggs into a warmed glass jar. Pour heated pickle mixture over eggs.
They'll pickle quicker when warm.
Let jar cool and place into refrigerator at least 4 to 5 days.
The longer the eggs stay in juice the more they will pickle.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top of batter.
Bake an hour or until brown in 325° oven.

title: wassail
directions: Place spices in net bag. Heat juices. Add sugar, water and tea. Add spices. Do not boil. Serve hot.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle over all 1 cup of sugar.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix well before serving.

title: garbage cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for batter.
Mix remaining ingredients in another bowl for topping.
In greased pan, put in layer of topping, then add 1/2 of first batter, then another of topping and the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: turkey sausage, peppers and onions
directions: Place sausage links in skillet with 1/4-inch water.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Uncover; cook until liquid is absorbed and sausages are browned.
Set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add onions, peppers and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add sausage, cover and cook on low for 10 minutes.
Serve on Italian rolls.

title: prize winning sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix soda and milk and add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Combine flour and salt; sift together.
Add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Take out.
Roll out and cut out cookies.
These puff up when baking so don't roll out too thick.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned broth. Cut chicken into small cubes as for chicken salad. Mix ingredients and put in a 3-quart oblong dish and refrigerate. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet gherkins
directions: First Day:
In the morning, wash cucumbers (stem end may be left on).
Drain cucumbers and place in large container.
Cover with boiling water.
In the afternoon (6 to 8 hours later, drain the cucumbers and cover with fresh boiling water.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese well.
Stir in remaining ingredients (shrimp last).
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Serve well on bed of lettuce.

title: chunky chicken salad(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine rotini, corn, red pepper, mushrooms, olives, celery, onion and cheese.
In small bowl, blend Italian dressing, mayonnaise and pepper.
Add to salad mixture; toss to coat. Gently stir in chicken.
Serve immediately to cover and chill.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Cut up small onion and simmer a few minutes in water (1/4 cup).
Add 1 cup tomato juice and bring to a slow boil.
Add gelatine and let dissolve thoroughly.
Remove from flame and add other tomato juice, vinegar, salt, pepper, celery, olives and pecans.
Put into mold or ring and serve on lettuce.
Nice at Christmastime.
Serves about 10 to 12 in small portions.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender and process.

title: carol's cranberry tea
directions: Wash cranberries.
Cook in 2 quarts water until berries pop; let stand for 5 minutes.
Strain cranberries and discard cranberry skins.
Add sugar, 2 cups water and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add orange juice and lemon juice. Stir.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sole, florentine style
directions: Wash spinach, remove stems and place in saucepan.
Cover and cook for a few minutes with a little salt and only the water on the spinach.
Drain; return to pan with 2 tablespoons butter and saute briefly.
Season with salt and pepper and pinch of nutmeg and set aside.
(If using frozen spinach, defrost, drain, then stir in butter and seasonings.)
Heat wine with 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper in a frying pan.
Poach the sole fillets for 30 seconds.
Remove from pan and let the sauce reduce to about 3 to 4 tablespoons.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook meat with onion and bell pepper in skillet until brown. Add to beans with brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes in oven or cook in microwave for about 15 minutes.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Saute onion and green pepper with hamburger, heating but not totally browned.
Season to taste.
Spread half of cabbage in baking dish.
Cover with ground beef mixture.
Add rest of cabbage. Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: baked seafood(delicious with walleye, cod, flounder, whitefish.)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thinly slice onions and saute in 2 tablespoons butter and sherry.
Set aside.
Place fillets in a large baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan and squeeze lemons over top.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with more cheese, salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Add onion and drippings.
Bake 10 more minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black bean dip
directions: Drain beans, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine beans, reserved liquid, chili powder, salt, pepper, cumin and hot pepper sauce in a blender.
Process until smooth.
Combine onion and garlic in a nonstick skillet or saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat until onion is soft and translucent.
Uncover and cook until slightly browned.
Add chilies and cook 3 minutes more. Add bean mixture and mix well. Garnish with pepper strips.
Serve with corn tortilla chips. Serve hot or cold, either way it's delicious!

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Before serving, set out to room temperature, 30 minutes.

title: smothered pheasant
directions: Cut pheasant (about 2 1/2 pounds) in quarters and rub with butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Place, skin side down, on cold broiler grid.
Broil 3 inches from full gas flame 20 minutes, basting several times with melted butter or margarine.
Turn and continue broiling 15 minutes, basting several times with melted butter or margarine.
One pheasant makes 2 large servings.

title: boiled fudge frosting
directions: Boil 2 minutes and cool.
Beat and add vanilla.
Spread on cake.

title: portuguese spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach in water already on washed leaves (briefly).
Chop fine.
Cook onion in butter.
Add the spinach, stock and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in egg (well beaten).
Cook until lightly thickened, without boiling.
Sprinkle with Parmigiano Reggiano.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together except for shortening.
Roll into 2-inch balls and roll in flour.
Heat shortening and brown meatballs.
Place in casserole and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello
in
cups
boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Chill until firm.
Put into large mixing bowl and beat.
When
broken
up well, add Cool Whip or Dream Whip and the juice
from
pineapple.
Stir
in 2 cans of drained mandarin oranges
and
drained,
crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into
serving dish and sprinkle with nuts. Cool and serve.
Cut into squares.

title: white (sugar) cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding flour a little at a time. Form into 3 rolls. Refrigerate thoroughly. Slice about 1/4 inch thick. Sprinkle with sugar (colored sugar is a great hit with kids). Bake 10 minutes or until lightly brown at 350°.

title: cornmeal turnovers
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add cornmeal.
Combine with egg, shortening and milk.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Pat into a sheet 1/2-inch thick.
Cut as for cookies.
Brush tops with melted butter and fold half over. Place on well-oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form ball.
Roll in slivered almonds.
Chill and serve.

title: adils' dam aly(steamed potatoes)
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 10 minutes.
Drain and peel.
Pour 2 cups vegetable oil into deep skillet with oil for deep frying. Heat until 350° and fry potatoes for 2 minutes in 3 batches.
Brown all sides.
Put on paper towel and stub with toothpick.
Heat oil and in other skillet, add ginger and chili and fry.
Add salt, red pepper, garam masala, cumin, turmeric and coriander.
Stir in yoghurt and water and bring to boil.
Add potatoes and reduce heat and cook.
Put on tight lid; simmer for 20 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes, then uncover.
Sprinkle remaining garam masala on top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Chill.
Take loaf of rye bread and hollow it out.
Fill with dip.
Use cubes of rye bread for the dip.
Have toothpicks available.

title: apricot and pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello and bring to a full boil, then cool completely.
When cool, add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour in glass 12 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate until set.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with 24 cupcake liners.
Put a wafer in each.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla. Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Chill. Top each with pie filling.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Arrange a layer of the combined cracker and bread crumbs in the bottom of it, then a layer of oysters, butter in small pieces, salt and pepper.
Repeat, having a layer of crumbs on top with small pieces of butter dotted over them. Have only 2 layers of oysters.
Moisten with milk and oyster liquor combined.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pack in round bowl and chill overnight.

title: india curry
directions: Fry onions, chili and curry powder in enough fat to brown.
Add salted meat and press flat in frying pan; brown on both sides. Chop into small pieces and add to tomatoes, beans and diced potatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Bring salted rice to boil and boil for 15 minutes.
Serve on plates with sauce on top.
Serves 6. Serve with Fritos.

title: crunchy apple breakfast or dessert
directions: Core and slice the apple.
Add water and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or you could microwave 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, vanilla, yogurt and sugar.
Put on top of baked apple mixture.
Sprinkle Grape-Nuts and nutmeg on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in dishpan in order given.
Drop on cookie sheet by the teaspoonful and flatten.
Bake for 12 minutes. Do not overbake.
(There is no flour in this recipe.)

title: chinese-japanese over rice
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables.
Cook over medium heat until thawed and tender. Add soup and allow to simmer at least 45 minutes. Cook rice and serve over rice.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Boil cherry cola in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat until reduced to 1 1/2 cups, about 45 minutes.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer until mixture is reduced to 2 1/2 cups, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes. Transfer glaze to large bowl.
(Can be made 1 week ahead.
Cover; chill.
Bring to room temperature before using.)

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Stir in chopped onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange squash, cheese and bread in alternate layers in buttered baking dish.
Beat egg and milk together.
Pour over layers in casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot ham and cheese wrap-ups
directions: Cut ham and cheese into 1/4-inch cubes.
Combine ham, cheese, eggs and olives.
Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce together and pour over ham mixture.
Toss until well blended.
Pile mixture into split rolls.
Wrap in squares of foil.
Store in freezer.
Heat in foil in 350° to 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until filling is hot and rolls are crusty.

title: tuna casserole #1
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Gently mix all other ingredients together.
Place in 300° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: skillet spaghetti(in a hurry try this)
directions: In Dutch oven or large deep skillet, brown first 4 ingredients in shortening.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stir in water.
Bring mixture to boil; add spaghetti.
Cook uncovered 12 to 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir in tomatoes and ketchup.
Simmer about 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings, about 8 cups.

title: bachelor's stew
directions: Cook rice according to standard convention (white, brown, wild, preferably, not Minute rice).
When rice is cooked, add soup. Stir in the curry powder to taste.
Serve with bread and milk for a bachelor's balanced diet. Gets better with age!

title: little chocolate fudge cups
directions: Melt chocolate in butter or margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon in tiny baking cups.
Cook at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: transparent cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat together last 3 ingredients and pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: polish biga's(polish sausage and sauerkraut)
directions: Drain sauerkraut and add 2 cups water, caraway seed and sugar. Boil 10 minutes.
Soak yellow split peas for 1 hour in 1 cup cold water.
Boil until thick; add to sauerkraut.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter; add to sauerkraut mixture.
Season with pepper.
Set aside.
Boil sausage for 1 hour in a little water. Take out and brown slightly in butter.
Cut into 8 pieces and arrange on top of the sauerkraut.
Serve with whole small potatoes, topped with fresh butter and dill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Let zucchini and salt stand for 30 minutes.
Grease dish with butter.
Mix all other ingredients; add zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut whirls
directions: Cream first five ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on wax paper. Melt chocolate chips.
Cool and spread onto dough.
Roll into log. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Slice with a sharp knife. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread mixture on ham slices.
Roll up.
Place seam sides down on tray and refrigerate until chilled.
Slice and place on snack crackers.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Mix Blue cheese dressing, mayo, sugar, vinegar and pepper until blended well. Set aside. Cut apple slices in half (or chopped apple is fine). Combine apple, cabbage and grapes. Add dressing and toss to coat well.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in double boiler or microwave.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Mix into melted candy, the can of condensed milk.
Pour in enough whole milk to thin candy mixture.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Finish filling with whole milk to fill line. Stir real good before closing lid.
Freeze.

title: low-fat cheese-garlic biscuits(just like red lobster's)
directions: Mix ingredients until a soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush hot biscuits with mixture of 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder and 3 tablespoons reduced fat margarine.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: rainbow stew
directions: Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Divide mixture into three containers. Add food coloring to all three. Place small amounts of rainbow stew into several Ziploc bags. Reinforce closure with packing tape.
Let the children write on bags with the fingers.
They can also mix two colors together and discover a new color. If you want to extend their shelf life, refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, mayonnaise
and
red pepper and mix well.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup
of pecans in an oiled 7-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold
on
platter
and
pat remaining pecans
onto
cheese
ring.
Garnish
with
parsley sprigs. Serve on crackers
with
strawberry preserves on top, if desired. This is pretty with preserves served in center of ring.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice off top of tomato.
Hollow out tomatoes, saving the pulp.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl, using your hands to mix (using the tomato pulp).
Stuff tomatoes; top with shredded cheese and chill for about 30 minutes before serving.
Good served with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and blend well.
Shape into a loaf and place in a 2-quart casserole. Combine the last 3 ingredients together and pour over meat loaf.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wilma's egg pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if you prefer. Bake at 350°.

title: pull apart whole wheat bread
directions: Cream shortening with sugar, reserve about 1 tsp. sugar.
Add yeast to warm water with reserved sugar.
Add egg, salt, yeast, water and bran to creamed mixture.
Add flour.
Place in bowl and let rise until double.
Knead lightly and form into small balls. Roll in melted butter.
Stack in greased bundt pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake 45 minutes at 350.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water (use warm water for dry yeast). Pour scalded milk over shortening, salt and molasses.
Stir until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir 1 cup flour in.
Add softened yeast and oats.
Stir in enough more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board; knead until satiny, about 10 minutes.
Round dough into ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top lightly with melted shortening.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down; let stand 10 minutes.
Place in pans. Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: adobong okra
directions: Wash and parboil the okra in water.
Set aside.
Fry the pork. Push to one side of the pan. Saute garlic, onion and okra. Season with vinegar, patis and pepper.
Cook until okra is tender-crisp.
(Vinegar cuts sliminess of okra.)

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll on a floured board and cut.
Place in a greased baking pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 medium-sized biscuits.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Add cream cheese to chicken; mix well.
Spread mixture on each roll.
Roll up and bake according to directions on can of rolls.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Put ground meat to brown and strain. Put noodles in an oven pan. Mix ground meat and cheese together and put over noodles. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top to your taste. Put in 350° oven and cook until cheese is melted for about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt together oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Then add buttermilk, eggs, soda, and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased 11 x 16 pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Start making frosting 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: quality fruit punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large container.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill until serving time.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir gently to mix.

title: aunt minnie's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour with nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice and soda.
Mix alternately with buttermilk.
Add blackberry jam, raisins and chopped pecans.
Grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Stir thoroughly.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir in flour until batter is very stiff.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: yellow cake
directions: Beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes the flour, sugar, 3/4 cup milk, Crisco and salt.
Stir in baking powder and add 1/2 cup milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix thoroughly by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes more.
Pour into two (9 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans which have been rubbed with Crisco or lined with wax paper.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Rinse spinach, leaving leaves damp. Steam spinach for 2 minutes; set aside. In a large pan, saut onion, garlic, oregano and basil in oil until onion is soft. Add tomatoes. Cover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes. Cook lasagna noodles per package directions; drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In casserole dish melt one-half stick margarine.
Add Ritz crackers.
Mix well and put back in cup.
Melt remaining margarine in the same casserole dish.
Add Velveeta cheese and melt slowly. Cook broccoli, drain well and add cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: ruth's dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add milk gradually, creaming well.
Add pudding mix; blend well.
Beat until thick.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cake.
Drain pineapple; spread over pudding layer.
Spread dessert topping over pineapple layer.
Garnish with nuts and red cherries, if desired.
One-half large box yellow cake mix may be used.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown sausage well, adding onion to sausage when about half done.
Drain well.
Mix all other ingredients with sausage and onion.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pieces and pat into thin rounds on baking sheet.
Spread biscuit rounds with sausage mixture.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Drop rounds into Ziploc bag when frozen.
When ready to serve, place desired number on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° approximately 10 minutes.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Fill large pot 2/3 full with water.
Bring to boil and add salt, shrimp boil and potatoes.
Cover and boil 10 minutes.
Add onions.
Boil 10 minutes and add sausage.
Boil 10 minutes and add corn.
Boil 10 minutes and add shrimp.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain water and serve.

title: super hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients, store in airtight container.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, the sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed banana, shortening, margarine or butter and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: sausage crescents
directions: Cook sausage links according to package directions; drain well.
Cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent roll dough into triangles.
Place 1 sausage link at wide end of each triangle; roll up.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until crescent is golden brown.
Serve, if desired, with mustard dip.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until golden brown.

title: gooey coffee cake
directions: Mix 2 well beaten eggs with yellow cake mix and 1 stick melted butter.
This
will be sticky like a dough.
Spread in the bottom of a greased and floured cake pan.
May have to use fingers.
Then mix
the
powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 well beaten eggs
and vanilla in a blender until smooth and pour on top of the other. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked trout
directions: Soak trout in Tender Quick solution 8 to 12 hours.
Rinse thoroughly.
Place trout on smoker and smoke for 3 hours or until done (fish will flake easily).
Debone and serve with cream cheese and Ritz crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Place in casserole and cover with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
I usually put some slivered almonds on top.

title: sea mist
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and champagne.
Yields 5 quarts.
Serving Size:
20. Preparation Time:

title: lo-fat cornbread
directions: Add enough milk to ingredients to moisten.
Spray with Pam and cook until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until liquid is gone.
Stir once or twice to mix well while casserole is cooking.

title: easter egg bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease large ovenproof skillet or large shallow baking dish; set aside.
Fry sausage in a skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain and transfer to bowl.
Wipe out skillet. Add butter and melt over medium heat.
Saute mushrooms and onions until soft but not brown.
Remove from heat and stir in sausage. Blend remaining ingredients and turn into the prepared dish.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Makes an excellent main dish for a special breakfast or brunch.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a bowl with a lid. Cut all biscuits into quarters and shake to coat all pieces.
In a pan, boil 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon with the butter. Put half of the biscuits into a tube pan.
Pour half of the butter mixture over it.
Layer the rest of the biscuits; pour on the rest of the butter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Invert onto plate within 5 minutes.

title: egg souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Layer sausage, cheese and bread.
Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and cream of mushroom soup; pour over layers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour.
Put pan of water on shelf under dish.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup.
Add cream cheese.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water; add to soup mixture and beat with wire whip to mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased mold. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Mix with chopped vegetables.
Toss with dressings and Salad Supreme seasoning to taste.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. While hot, add Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Cool 30 minutes. Add pineapple and orange juice.
Freeze Mixture.
Allow punch to partially thaw several hours before needed.
Add one 2 liter ginger ale.
Mix punch and ginger ale to form a delicious slush.

title: chutney
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Cook in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck. Mix all ingredients, except Tater Tots. Put in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Place Tater Tots on top of casserole and bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: quick potato casserole
directions: Place in 2-quart casserole with 2 layers of string beans/potatoes/onions/soup.
Cover and cook at 325° until potatoes are done, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Put in greased casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with baked ham!

title: pineapple bake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of 9 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Combine sugar and flour and pour over pineapple.
Top with Velveeta cheese (regular Cheddar gets chewy).
Sprinkle crushed crackers over mixture.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix and shape in bowl or can and chill in refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2. Beat dry cake mix, brown sugar and peanut butter in a large bowl, on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of the crumbly mixture.
Beat remaining crumbling mixture, water, oil and egg on low speed, scraping the bowl constantly, until moistened. Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Stir nuts into the 2/3 cup crumbling mixture, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, bananas, nuts and strawberries.
Pour half in mold. Leave the rest out.
Refrigerate mold.
After it sets, spread sour cream over top and put on rest of jello mixture and return to refrigerator.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix yolks and other ingredients, not paprika.

title: coconut oat drops
directions: Beat egg, add sugar gradually, then melted shortening and vanilla.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: chocolate chip butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; sift flour and soda.
Add together and cream.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Spoon by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into pastry with blender or fork.
Stir in milk with fork or spoon.
Squeeze off 1 1/2 to 2-inch ball, roll and shape.
Place onto baking pan and bake in a 425° oven until golden brown.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add milk and coconut.
Spoon drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put candy in and shut off oven.
When they cool down, they're done.

title: matt's favorite chocolate cheesecake
directions: Melt together 1 pound chocolate and butter. Cool and

stir in sour cream. Beat cream cheese and sugar. Add eggs slowly and vanilla. Slowly beat in chocolate. Pour into baked crust. Bake 1 hour at 325° in a water bath. Remove. Cool. Glaze with 4 ounces chocolate and cream, melted together and cooled slightly. Sprinkle with cocoa powder.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop celery and onion; add to a small amount of boiling water (to cover celery and onion) and simmer to soften while peeling and cubing potatoes (I use Russets).
Add salt to water, then add potatoes and more boiling water, just to cover potatoes.
Boil until desired consistency.
Reduce heat.
Add canned milk to the existing potato mixture and water.
Add cube of margarine and slowly heat soup.
Stir often; add white pepper and salt to desired taste.
When margarine is melted, soup will be ready.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine egg yolks with remaining ingredients; cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: mrs. ledbetter's chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter, stirring to blend, in top of double boiler (or microwave on High for about 1 minute, stir to blend). Cool slightly.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Wash peanuts and place in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Add salt.
Boil until tender.
Let stand in same water until cool.

title: kahlua
directions: You will need 2 quart empty bottles with screw on lids.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches. Leave whole. Put cloves and cinnamon loosely in a clean, thin white cloth and tie top tightly. Simmer spices, sugar, vinegar and water for 10 minutes or until sugar dissolves and mixture becomes spicy. Add peaches and cook slowly until tender but not broken. Let sit overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Combine sugar, onion, mayonnaise, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in squash.
Place in buttered dish.
Sprinkle cheese on.
Put cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Put 1/2 cup butter on top of crackers.
Bake on 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple kuchen cake
directions: Mix all together.
Add 2 cups of chopped apples and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Put into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle a mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry juliet
directions: Put frozen juice and strawberries along with two orange juice cans of cold water in blender and mix for 30 to 45 seconds.
Add additional water, if desired.
Serve in juice glasses.

title: crab mornay en casserole
directions: Into individual casseroles, pour 1/2 cup cream sauce to which wine has been added.
Add layer of 1/2 cup crabmeat and top with a slice of cheese.
Sprinkle each casserole with paprika and butter. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes and serve hot. Serves 4.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour an 8 1/2 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Combine the eggs, oil, carrot, pineapple, vanilla, sugar and cereal in a large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: armenian rice
directions: Saute onion and bacon.
Add butter and rice.
Fry 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium-low heat until rice is tender.
Serves 12.

title: low calorie salad or dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in one small package dry jello. Chill in refrigerator.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; fold in Cool Whip.
Top with fresh cooked blueberries or pie filling.
Chill and cut in squares to serve.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour and sugars; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture; press remaining firmly in bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking dish and up sides.
Stir nuts into reserved crumb mixture; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients (except crumb mixture).
Mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add boiling water and stir well. Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with 2 beaten egg whites for meringue.
Brown lightly in oven on broil.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the sugar and flour.
In saucepan mix margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar. Mix well.
Add remaining 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour in a greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Begin making icing about 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: gobbly gooks
directions: Put butter, milk, cocoa, peanut butter, sugar, vanilla and salt in pot and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in bowl with Chex and flour.
Put on cookie sheet.
Let cool in refrigerator.
When cooled (if wanted), put powdered sugar on top.
Enjoy.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown onions, celery and garlic in stew pot.
Add all other ingredients; cook at low boil for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.

title: banana-pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple chunks into saucepan.
Bring juice to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour.
Cook until thick, then set off heat.
Add 2 egg yolks and cook again slightly.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Add to cooked mixture.
Cool.
Add pineapple chunks and sliced bananas and fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: crispy coconut balls
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
With buttered hands, shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut, pressing gently to coat.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Chop hard-boiled eggs,	mix with crab meat, add rest of ingredients and 1/2
cup
of bread crumbs to mixture, save 1/2 for topping, place flour, milk and butter in small saucepan to make cream sauce,
mix
with
crab meat and other ingredients. Fill crab shells,
sprinkle with small amount of bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven until topping is brown.

title: chow chow
directions: Prepare vegetables and chop fine.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and press out all liquid, if possible.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 hours over low flame.
Stir frequently.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: caramel frosting for cake
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar
and water in saucepan.
Place over low heat; stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil hard for
1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Gradually
add 10x sugar, beating until smooth after each addition.
Cool
to spreading consistency.	Makes enough for 2 layers or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off any fat.
Add mushrooms, onion and green pepper and saute until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan (use margarine or spray with Pam).
When all ingredients are cooked, make layers in pan, alternating noodles, cottage cheese, sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and sauce.
When you reach the top of pan, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Cut carrots into thin pieces.
Thinly slice onion.
Cut broccoli into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cut in the Crisco.
Stir in the milk.
Turn out on floured surface.
Flatten dough and cut out the biscuits.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° to 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour and the next 7 ingredients together with fork; blend.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Bake in 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Store at room temperature.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except marshmallows and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour marshmallows on top (small) while cake is hot.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into pan you will bake in (8 x 8-inch).
Make 3 holes in mixture; in first hole put in the vinegar, in second hole the melted shortening, and in the third hole the vanilla.
Next put in the cold water and mix well. Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add mustard, salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and milk. Layer in a long Pyrex dish as follows:
bread, sausage, cheese and egg mixture.
For best results, allow to set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: clamcakes
directions: Add
all
ingredients to the beaten eggs.
Mixture will be runny.
Pour
onto	griddle
until	brown.	Makes 36 dollar size cakes.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: mushrooms and wild rice
directions: Sprinkle sliced mushrooms with lemon juice, then saute in butter until just tender (do not brown).
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream; add nutmeg.
Form prepared rice into a ring on a plate.
Serve mushroom mixture inside ring.
Best if served immediately.

title: ham spread
directions: Use food processor to finely chop meats.
Add eggs and process for only seconds.
Remove mixture and add relish and mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.
Very good on party rye or pumpernickel bread.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Layer in order in greased casserole dish.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Cut in pie shape.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell peppers until onion is clear on low fire.
Add flour and water.
Cook, covered, on low fire until celery is tender.
Add crawfish and fat.
Cook about 20 minutes. Serve over hot rice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and destem mushrooms.
Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and bacon bits together.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture and bake in oven until brown and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: creamy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice into a greased shallow 3-quart baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch); set aside. In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup of the butter; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add milk, bouillon, seasoned salt, garlic powder and pepper. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat. Add chicken, cheese and sour cream. Stir until the cheese is melted. Pour over rice. Melt remaining butter; toss with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: granny's pixie pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon rosemary chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Cover bottom of pan with lemon juice, approximately 1/4-inch deep.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Sprinkle with rosemary.
Turn chicken with fork a few times to mix.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and broil to brown about 5 minutes on each side.

title: million dollar cream pie
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, coconut and chopped pecans. Mix together well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: prego lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on box; drain. Rinse with cold water.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Combine onion mixture in a bowl with chopped chicken and green chilies.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch margarine greased pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, eggs and 10x sugar.
Pour over other cake mixture.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together dry items.
Add milk and oil. Stir.
Put into pie plate and pat into shape (no need to roll out).
Great for quiche, pumpkin pie or anything that requires pie shell only.

title: chicken with wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Place raw rice and seasoning mix on bottom of baking dish.
Place raw chicken on top of rice.
Mix hot water and cream of mushroom soup together and pour over raw chicken.
Place in oven. Bake, covered, with foil for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil and bake 1 hour.
Add water if dry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Put cracker crumbs on top and melt margarine; pour on top of crumbs. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cook at 350° until it starts to bubble real good.

title: frosted 7-up salad
directions: Cook
until
real
thick
and cool completely. Then mix with 2 cups
Cool Whip.
Then spread on top of Jell-O mixture (more like a dessert).
Real good!

title: lazy man cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in
boiling
water
and cook until slightly soft. Drain.
Brown ground
beef
and
onion
until
onion is clear and beef loses its pink color.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce and water to
meat.
Prepare
Minute
rice as per directions on package and
add to meat mixture.
Layer cabbage and meat mixture, 2 layers of
each,
in a 11 x 15-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Heat juice.
Dissolve jello in juice and add sherbet until melted.
Add fruits and pour in mold.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter, add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mix in dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (loaf pan) or 375° (long pan).

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Roll soda crackers until fine.
Add to mixture.
Stir in nutmeats.
Spread in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand in stoneware bowl.
Roll into balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Keep bacon drippings.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put rest of meat mixture on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: watermelon basket
directions: Carve a country basket from a watermelon.
Place melon with flattest side down.
With a large knife, cut a 2-inch wide handle halfway through the melon.
Cut horizontally from each end to handle.
With melon ball cutter, scoop out insides.
Halve cantaloupe and make balls.
Combine fruit and honey in a bowl. Spoon into basket and garnish with fresh mint.
Edges of basket may be trimmed into points or scallops.

title: sesame parmesan chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, add some minced garlic, spreading onto chicken.
Sprinkle parmesan and sesame seed on chicken, and place in frying pan with 1 T. olive oil, and 1/2 c. water.
Cover and simmer until completely dry and caramelized coating forms.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cut angel food cake into slightly thin pieces and place in bottom of container.
Mix Dream Whip and milk (provided on package) together.
After this is mixed, add cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup milk in with Dream Whip.
Combine all together.
Spread part of this over the layer of cake.
Place some of the filling over this. Do another layer of cake and do the same with the mixture and then the berries on top.
Cool before serving.

title: low-fat applesauce cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix vegetable oil, applesauce, sugars, egg and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Then stir in oats and raisins and mix all well.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°. Serves 36; 1.1 grams fat per cookie.

title: garden lasagna
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add next 6 ingredients (zucchini, onion, carrots, celery, garlic and stewed tomatoes).
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in next 7 ingredients (tomato sauce, paste, parsley, seasoning, basil, salt and pepper).
Bring to a boil, stirring to break up tomatoes into pieces.
Reduce heat, cover and bring to a boil.
Boil until liquid is reduced to approximately 5 cups.
Cook noodles (when made ahead of time, don't cook).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/4 of cooked sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with layer of noodles.
Top with 1/3 Ricotta cheese or cottage cheese, then 1/4 Parmesan cheese. Repeat this process two times.
Spread remaining sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Set aside 5 minutes before cutting.
May freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Use 1/2 cup nuts to roll cheese ball in.
Chill overnight.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until leaves are wilted.
Mix remaining ingredients except last one.
Fold it in leaves and put in a baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over cabbage.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg with electric mixer until fluffy. In separate bowl, mix bananas and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture alternately with banana mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into prepared loaf pan or muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour (for loaf) or 15 to 20 minutes (for muffins), until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pinto enchiladas
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mash by hand or electric mixer.
Heat through.
Fill tortillas with bean filling.
Place, seam side down, in 13-inch baking dish, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover the top only small amount of tomato sauce.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325° or until heated through.
Top with tomato sauce and Pimiento Cheese Spread.
Serves 6.

title: surprise crackles
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in saucepan.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Add the sugar, eggs and vanilla to the chocolate-butter mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Cover and chill dough overnight. You can add nuts to dough before chilling.
Heat oven to 350°. Shape dough into small balls.
Put powdered sugar in medium bowl. Roll cookie balls in it to coat completely.
Place on greased baking sheet about 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake about 8 minutes. Remove pan from oven and take cookies from baking sheet to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 90 cookies.

title: extra virgin delight
directions: Heat olive oil to hot.
Add cleaned peeled and deveined shrimp, clams and broccoli.
Cook until shrimp and broccoli are tender.
Prepare linguini al dente.
Mix extra virgin mix with pasta.
Garnish with red pepper.
Voila!

title: creme of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package.
Take handle of wooden spoon and make holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and creme of coconut over cake.
Top with drained pineapple and Cool Whip. Cover Cool Whip with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together.
Mix the jello and water together and pour over the ingredients and put in the refrigerator until set.

title: south 21 slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage on the side of the grater that has the long slots. Chop the onions pretty fine and mix with other ingredients. Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Will keep for several days.

title: peanut chicken soup
directions: In large pan, heat oil on medium; add onion, green peppers and garlic.
Stir 5 minutes until tender.
Add tomatoes and juice (break up tomatoes with fingers).
Stir in peanut butter until peanut butter dissolves.
Add pepper and chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Reduce to simmer; cover and cook 40 minutes, until rice is done, then add chicken and cook 10 minutes longer. Serve each bowl garnished with parsley.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Heat and add to jello.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add cold ginger ale slowly. Let partially gel in refrigerator.
Stir in cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Let set until gelled.
Top with Dream Whip topping. Prepare Dream Whip per package instructions and add 1 package cream cheese (left at room temperature).
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: winter day potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes; drain but save water.
Saute bacon and onion until brown.
Mash potatoes; add bacon and onion, parsley, salt, nutmeg and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in milk.
Heat over low flame. Sprinkle with cheese.
Add reserved water if soup is too thick.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
In a baking dish, mix all ingredients except chops.
Place chops on top.
Cover and bake in oven at 375° for one hour or until done, turning chops once after 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: apricot crunch
directions: Layer apricots, crackers, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Repeat with several layers.
Pour juice from apricots over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is very good with pork or can be used as dessert.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Slice carrots, onion and zucchini.
Steam vegetables for 5 minutes; set aside.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Mix this into vegetables and set aside.
Mix stuffing mix with melted oleo.
Pat 1/2 of this mixture into bottom of round or square pan or casserole dish.
Fill casserole dish with vegetable mixture; top with rest of stuffing mixture.
Sprinkle pepper over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (or until nicely brown).
Makes a nice side dish for holiday meals.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: In saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Add chocolate and continue cooking, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla. Chill 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into crust and chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: bickford's baked apple pancake
directions: In one bowl, combine 2 medium apples (peeled, cored and sliced), light brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter or margarine.
In a second bowl, combine the flour, milk, eggs and a pinch of salt.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 2 extra tablespoons of butter in a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour in flour mixture; place apple mixture in center.
Bake for 15 minutes.
You will get a pleasant surprise when you open the oven.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and black pepper.
Cook noodles and drain; add green pepper and steak sauce.
Add cooked noodles to ground beef mixture and bouillon cubes dissolved in boiling water. Add garlic salt; mix well.
Cover and let simmer slowly, about 1 hour.
Before serving, add sour cream.
Stir in, cover and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: In deep baking dish, sprayed with vegetable spray (Pam), place 2 cups of sliced zucchini (1/4-inch thick) evenly across bottom. Add onion, ham and Parmesan cheese.
In blender, thoroughly blend eggs, milk, Bisquick and seasonings.
Pour over zucchini mix. Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes or until center is set.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients and milk, alternating.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: old fashioned sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add cinnamon.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add flour and sweet potatoes, then vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: frozen berry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; stir in frozen berries until all is thawed.
Add applesauce and refrigerate to set.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Grease a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Put in a layer of shredded cheese, then a layer of peppers cut in strips or chopped, then cheese and peppers and a layer of cheese on top.
Beat eggs; add flour, milk and a pinch of salt.
Pour over cheese layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 8 minutes; cut in small squares.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add oysters, cooking about 1 1/2 minutes or until edges begin to curl.
Add milk and cook until hot (do not boil).
Add salt and pepper and stir.
Serve hot.

title: spinach-and-onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 8-inch round baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
In large skillet, saute onions in oil 5 minutes until very tender.
Set aside.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to boil sugar, cocoa, margarine and 1/2 cup milk.
After boiling, put in vanilla, then put oats in and bring to boil.
To a thick mixture, add peanut butter.
Put on waxed paper by the spoonful.
Wait a few minutes, then enjoy.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Stir all together.
Serve hot in chafing dish (or fondue) with large Fritos or crackers.
(I used Sociables crackers and it was delicious.)

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients together with a mixer on low speed, until just blended. Increase speed to medium and beat for 4 minutes. Stir in pecans. Wrap and refrigerate about 2 hours. Roll into 1-inch balls and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 15 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: turkey-vegetable soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add water, bouillon cubes, turkey and vegetables.
Boil gently, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Stir a little milk into the flour until mixture is smooth. Add remaining milk, salt and pepper.
Add to soup.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking until soup is slightly thickened.

title: cherie's campfire beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes, stirring several times.

title: 7-up eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients well and beat with mixer for 2 minutes. Serve very cold.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add
the	remaining
ingredients. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn your oven
back to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Very good,
spicy
pumpkin
pie. Makes 2 nice 9-inch pies.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan; heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Gradually add to dry ingredients, beat 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make stiff dough.
Turn out; knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap and then towel. Let rest 20 minutes.
Punch down; divide.
Can be put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days or make rolls and freeze.

title: dinner burgers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Remove from pan and brown onion and green pepper in same pan.
Drain off fat.
Add ketchup, water and seasonings.
When mixture begins to simmer, return hamburgers to pan.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add more water if needed. Remove burger to platter and put sauce over them.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Blend the whipped cream and cooled pudding together.
Fold well drained fruits into pudding mixture with the marshmallows and bananas.
Chill salad thoroughly before serving.

title: easy pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients at the same time with mixer.
Mixture will be thick.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cake is done or cream cheese frosting is also very good.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Blend eggs, condensed milk and sugar together well with whisk spatula.
Add flavorings and salt.	Mash bananas with fork into pulp and stir into mixture.
Add milk until fill line in freezer is reached.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Rinse and drain dried beef slices; chop beef and spread on bottom of baking dish. Wrap each chicken breast in one half piece bacon. Place chicken over beef; blend soup and sour cream until smooth; pour over chicken. Bake at 300° for 2 hours covered, and 350° for 30 minutes more, uncovered.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add eggs and buttermilk. Mix together well.
Best to use iron skillet.
Put Crisco in iron skillet; heat in oven until melted.
Add about half of melted Crisco to cornbread mix; mix well.
Pour into iron skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: white chocolate delight
directions: Melt white chocolate with Crisco in double boiler over medium heat until smooth.
Dip Ritz Bits in melted chocolate.
Lay on wax paper to cool.
Good!!!

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles, then drain.
In a large skillet, cook and stir meat, onions and celery until meat is brown and onions are tender. Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, then simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pour cherry mix into 8 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherry mix.
Pour melted butter over all mixture.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls. Press down lightly. Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned. Serve hot or cold.

title: savory cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into 50 meatballs. Place in shallow baking pan; broil until brown, turning once. Spoon off fat.
In saucepan, cook pepper and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Beat together the eggs, evaporated milk and flour.
In greased pan, alternate half the chilies and half the cheeses twice.
Top with egg mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour tomato sauce on top and bake another 15 minutes.
I use salsa on top.

title: chocolate peanut butter mickey mouse cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in small bowl.
Beat butter, peanut butter, sugars and vanilla in a large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup of morsels and oats.
Freeze until slightly firm, but not hard.
Make 1 1/2-inch balls; press down lightly on ungreased cookie sheet. Roll into 1 1/4; cut in
half.
Attach to first ball as ears. Repeat with remaining dough.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown and centers are soft. Let stand 3 minutes; remove to wire racks and cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine eggs, sugar and oil; beat well in a large bowl.
Sprinkle flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt very evenly over wet mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cream oleo with powdered sugar.
Beat until real fluffy and spread over crust.
Slice 4 large bananas over creamy layer. Drain pineapple and put over banana layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle nuts; chill.
Top with cherries and nuts (optional).

title: biscuit-meatball pie
directions: Combine beaten egg and 1/4 cup water.
Stir in bread crumbs, parsley, salt and dash of pepper.
Add ground beef, mix well. Shape mixture into 24 (1-inch) balls.

title: peaches and cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease the muffin tin.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, and salt.
Stir to mix.
In a medium bowl, beat together the eggs, sour cream, preserves, and oil.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of one of the muffins.
Remove muffins from pan immediately and cool slightly on rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon and stir in blueberries.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges.
Cut slits in top of crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients in an 8-quart pot.
Bring to boil. Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Strain the pulp and divide evenly between hot quart jars.
Pour in liquid evenly between jars.
Use all the liquid even though pulp may seem loosely packed; leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Process for 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: beef brisket in wine
directions: Salt & Pepper and coat brisket with flour; brown in skillet using cup of Italian Salad Dressing.
When very, very brown remove from skillet.
In 9x13-inch baking pan mix the 2 pkgs gravy mix and the 2 cups wine.
Add brisket; cover with foil and bake at 220° for about 4 hours or until very tender.
If necessary, add more wine. About one hour before brisket is finished cooking, slice large onion in thin slices and place on top of brisket.
Return to oven and cook the last hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 350° to 400° oven until golden brown.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine ingredients and roll very thin on floured surface. Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely.
Slice 1/4-inch wide. Unroll and spread out; let dry 2 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, cider vinegar, salad oil, salt and paprika.
Bring to a boil and then let cool.
Then pour over all other ingredients.
Let cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Combine margarine, onion, mustard and seed; mix well.
Spread on both sides of hamburger buns.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 cheese slice on bottom of each bun.
Cover with top bun. Wrap each sandwich in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; set aside.
Mix together and heat tomato soup, rice and water.
Add ground beef.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Chop cabbage in small pieces and layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour ground beef mixture over cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with grated cheese.
Return to oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes to melt cheese.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop enough stems for 1/3 cup.
Saute mushroom stems, green pepper and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill caps.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place liquid in coffeepot (percolator type) and dry ingredients in the basket.
Perk normal time.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricot halves in boiling water for 15 minutes, then cool.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Add apricots and water.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into apricot creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans just until blended.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick tests clean.
Glaze with apricot jam while still hot.
Probably my most asked for recipe.
Expensive, but worth it!

title: old fashioned ham and bean soup
directions: Cook ham in water 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Add celery and carrots to broth; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add ham, beans and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: master mix oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Put tomatoes in pan.
Bring to boil.
Add hamburger, onion and chili powder.
Turn down to about medium heat and let cook for about 2 hours or more.
Add meat tenderizer if wanted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until done.
Drain and mash.
Add all remaining ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Cream all of the cheeses together for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add all ingredients except sour cream (add eggs, one at a time).
Beat for 4 minutes more to blend all ingredients.
Fold in sour cream last.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in a 10-inch spring-form pan that has been buttered and floured.
Let cool in oven 3 to 5 hours.
Do not open oven door until time is up.

title: rolled sole
directions: Dip sole in milk, then in bread crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients and place 1 to 2 heaping spoonfuls in center of fillet.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add other liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large glass jar.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature 24 to 48 hours.
Stir occasionally. (Good only if mixture bubbles.)
Cover and refrigerate.
Warm to room temperature to use.
Warm to replenish every 7 to 10 days. To replenish, add 1 cup water, 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand at room temperature until mixture bubbles and then refrigerate.

title: baked onion-flavored chicken
directions: Grease bottom of shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle half the soup mix on bottom of dish.
Place chicken pieces over it, then drizzle margarine over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 425° oven for an hour or more.
Reserve pan juices (about 1/2 cup) and combine with sour cream.
Heat gently and serve with chicken.

title: tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Tips:
Potatoes may be filled ahead of time, covered and refrigerated until ready to bake.
If made ahead, add 3 to 4 tablespoons more milk to prevent drying and increase baking time to about 20 minutes.
Stuffed potatoes may also be heated in the microwave oven for 3 to 4 minutes on full power.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Top with slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all well; refrigerate overnight.
Serve as a dip for assorted crackers.

title: barbecued beef short ribs
directions: Brown ribs in hot lard. Combine flour and mustard; add remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked omelet
directions: Mix eggs, milk, cheese, salt and onion well.
Add cooled sausage (or uncooked links or ham).
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (glass dish at 325° for 40 minutes).
Serves 12.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Sprinkle half of chicken in pie crust.
Top with half of the onion, then half of the ham.
Repeat layers.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Blend in milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour over mixture in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: molasses bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour butter over cubes; toss.
Combine eggs, molasses, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Gradually stir in milk and vanilla.
Stir in raisins.
Pour entire mixture over the bread cubes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Serve warm, drizzled with heavy cream.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and zucchini.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in raisins and nuts; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
The bread can be frozen and is also good if spread with butter and cream cheese.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper; cook until tender.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Reserve 1/2 cup stock.
In a casserole dish, layer chicken, green beans, water chestnuts and onions.
Mix together soup, stock, curry powder and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and enough milk to make it soft enough to drop with a spoon.
Drop in hot fat and cook until brown.
Serve with butter.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour. While cake is still hot, poke holes in it with a fork or toothpick and pour icing over hot cake.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix broccoli with rice; add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add the chestnuts, which have been cut up into smaller pieces.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be topped with grated cheese or French fried onions before serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 5 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: steen's popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup and salt over low heat, stirring constantly.
When a few drops tested in cold water become brittle, add oleo and pour over popped corn.
Mix and shape into large balls.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam vegetables until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour bag of marshmallows in the pan and set aside.
In a large microwave-safe bowl add the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes on Medium temperature, then stir.
Repeat until all melted together.
Pour over marshmallows and spread evenly, mixing in the marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into small squares as this is very rich!

title: wine jello
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve sugar in boiling water, then add gelatin to boiling water.
Add wine and lemon juice. Pour in mold and place in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Rinse and drain
broccoli
well.
Cut
tops of broccoli from the stalks and put	in
a
large bowl.
If the stalks are large enough, peel them, then
slice the stalks and add to the broccoli tops.
Slice the
onion
rings.
Add to the broccoli. Add crumbled bacon and
top
with grated cheese.
Add dressing and toss just before serving.
Broccoli salad and dressing may be made the day before and refrigerated separately.

title: petal pink angel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare cake batter following package directions.
Fold in 1/2 tsp. almond extract.
Place 3 cups batter in medium bowl.
Fold in 3 drops red food coloring.
Spoon half of white batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover with pink batter.
