Top with remaining white batter.
Bake following package directions; cool.
Place whipping cream, gelatin and remaining almond extract in large bowl. Beat at medium speed.
Add confectioners sugar; beat at high speed until soft peaks form. Tint with 3 drops red food coloring.
Frost cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese thoroughly (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.

title: quick chili
directions: Cook garlic and meat in oil until meat is done.
Add sauce, salt and chili powder.
Stir, simmering over low heat, until desired thickness for about 45 minutes.
Dip off fat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy pumpkin dip
directions: In a food processor, process pumpkin and chickpeas until fairly smooth.
Add remaining ingredients to food processor and process until smooth.
Season to taste.
Serve with pita chips. Makes 3 cups.

title: beef stroganoff sandwiches
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine flour, milk and oleo; mixing well.
Add green beans before adding topping.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° in a preheated oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of oblong baking dish, completely covering pan.
Put dry cake mix on top of pie filling; completely cover with butter.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Blend all together.
Serve with cut up fruit of your choice. Delicious!

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook until syrup strings from spoon.
Pour half of mixture over egg whites.
Cook remaining syrup 2 minutes and pour over whites. Beat until mixture holds a peak.
Add nuts and vanilla and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and put into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put rhubarb over batter.
Pour whipping cream over rhubarb and sprinkle with the sugar and a little cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt
butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients by layers.
Cook
in pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: oriental salad
directions: *Available at Schnucks near deli.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Gradually stir in water. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat and add butter, lemon juice and peel. Serve warm or cool.

title: easy candy
directions: Melt chocolate and add marshmallows.
Roll in a round roll and roll in coconut.
Put in refrigerator to get hard and slice thin.

title: chicken pot pie(easy)
directions: Cut meat off breast bones and stir-fry slightly in oil about 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Put soup, drained Veg-All and 1/3 cup water into bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in chicken drained from oil.
Place in deep dish crusts (1/2 mixture in each).
Cover with regular crusts. Cut slits in top and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: kiwi strawberry tart
directions: Finely chop almonds and blend with butter, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, 1/2 tsp. almond extract and 1 1/2 c. flour.
Can be done in food processor.
Press mixture in tart pan, prick shell and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hungarian cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Add remaining ingredients to fat in pan.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cabbage should be tender, but crisp.
Crumble bacon over top before serving.

title: rhubarb surprise kuchen
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; cut in butter. Add egg and milk.
Mix well.
Press into greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Arrange rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle with Jell-O.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix meat, Ragu sauce, tomato paste, water, parsley, basil, oregano and garlic powder together.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: double chocolate fudge
directions: In double boiler melt semi-sweet chips with 2/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate chips with remaining Eagle Brand, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining walnuts.
Spread over fudge in pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: carter's coconut cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: creamy cottage dip
directions: Beat the cottage cheese, milk, instant onion and salt with electric mixer.
Stir in the pimiento and parsley.
Chill.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Four tablespoons equals 1 meat exchange.
Good on baked potatoes, too.

title: rice wine
directions: Place all ingredients in a large jar.
Leave for 14 days. Strain and bottle.
Cover tightly and store in a cool, dark place.

title: zesty green beans and cherry tomatoes
directions: In a 2-quart pan over medium heat, prepare green beans as label directs. Drain.
Add cherry tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low and heat until tomatoes are heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage rolls
directions: Beat together butter and cottage cheese until cheese is smooth.
Add salt and flour; beat by hand until elastic.
Chill overnight.

title: swedish kringler
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling point.
Remove from heat and add flour immediately, beating with a fork.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Add flavoring.
Spread 1st mixture and bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken pieces in 13 x 9 inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange onion slices over top.
In small saucepan, combine ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and liquid smoke.
Heat over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake chicken 1 hour or until juices run clear.
Discard onion slices.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy vegetable primavera
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry vegetables in oleo until tender-crisp.
Reduce heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Mix last 4 ingredients by hand in separate bowl, then add to first 6 ingredients.
Spread in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hummus(garbanzo bean dip)
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth in a food processor or with an electric mixer.
For a great sandwich, spread in a pita bread and fill with fresh vegetables.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Place green beans on a large square of double thickness foil. Season with sugar and pepper, if desired.
Top with lemon slices. Sprinkle with water chestnuts and green onion.
Dot with margarine.
Bring edges of foil up and, leaving a little space for expansion of steam, seal securely with a double fold.
Grill over slow coals, turning once, for 35 to 40 minutes or until beans are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze until dry.
Stir spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, chestnuts and green onions.
Blend well, cover and refrigerate 2 hours, stir before serving.

title: creamy fudge sauce
directions: Add chocolate to cream in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth and blended.
Add sugar, butter and salt and continue cooking, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes longer or until slightly thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve warm on ice cream, pudding or cake.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: pasta primavera
directions: For pesto, place fresh basil, red or green pepper, sour cream, grated Parmesan cheese,
salt,
garlic
and pepper in a blender. Cover; blend until
pureed.
Set
aside.
Place
10 cups water in 5 quart saucepan.
Add chicken, celery, bay leaf and other seasonings of your
choice.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and cook for
minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Discard celery and bay leaf.

title: new potato casserole
directions: Scrub
new potatoes; place in 2-inch deep casserole; add chopped
garlic,
olive oil, salt and pepper.
Mix well;
cover and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Turn over after 20 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add vegetable with sauce, chicken broth, cream and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together in a saucepan.
Add other ingredients
and cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thick enough to make rings when stirred.
Pour into the
baked pie
shell and cool.
Top with meringue or whipped cream before serving.

title: irish whole wheat soda bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Rub in butter.
Mix in buttermilk until dry ingredients are moist and away from sides of bowl.
(Mix with your hands.)
Knead on a floured board until smooth.
Flatten dough ball until it is 2-inches high.
Cut a cross on top with knife.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour on wire rack. (You can start baking on cookie sheet until bottom is firm enough for rack.) Delicious with corned beef and cabbage on St. Patrick's Day.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Early in the day, put all ingredients in a large bowl, one layer at a time, in the order given.
Cover and refrigerate.
Toss just before serving.

title: neiman-marcus chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box and spread over nuts in pan.
Cream the cheese, sugar and margarine together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Invert to serve.

title: chunky salsa cheese dip
directions: Over medium heat in saucepan, heat salsa enough to melt cheeses.
Serve hot or cold.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, cocoa and milk until well dissolved (3 minutes).
Put oats and peanut butter in bowl and mix well.
Add vanilla to cooked mixture and pour over oats and peanut butter. Mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add pie filling and bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin.
Remove from heat; stir until jello is dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple, lemon juice and Coke or Pepsi; stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and stir until thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; shred chicken. Mix chicken, soup and sour cream. Put into casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Spread crumb mixture over chicken mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: cream cheese crunch
directions: Mix well.
You may want to cut back on olives!

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan and pour mix in.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Slice in squares when cool.

title: german chocolate surprise
directions: Grease pan.
Sprinkle coconut and add nuts.
Add all of cake mix, then mix sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Drop by spoon over top of batter.
Bake by package directions.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on baking sheet and bake in moderate oven, 375°, for about 10 minutes.
Do not press them down; they will crack open.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into long roll (2 rolls are easier to handle) the size of a quarter.
Roll in sesame seed.
Chill, slice and bake as needed, about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat the brown sugar and shortening.
Stir in molasses and milk.
Mix the baking soda, flour, ginger and cloves.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook shells until soft, place in cold water and set aside.
Melt butter.
Add pork and beef; cook until brown.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until onion is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan, salt and bread crumbs.
Pour 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of casserole dish.
Stuff each shell and arrange on top of sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce and bake for 30 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine
sugar,
syrup, water and pinch of salt in pan. Bring to a rapid boil, cooking until this forms a soft ball in water. Beat
egg whites, pinch of salt and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl while liquid is cooking.
Remove liquid from stove and
pour
half over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Return remaining half
of liquid to stove and boil until a hard ball forms in water.
Liquid will be thick and look almost white at last
stage. Beat
first
mixture while last half is cooking, then
pour remaining into mixture beating slowly until mixture loses
its gloss
and
is stiff enough to drop by spoon.
Add nuts
and vanilla just before dropping onto waxed paper.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup
sugar, 1/2 cup oleo and beaten egg all together.
Mix rhubarb and 1 1/4 cups sugar together and put in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix water and soda together and sprinkle over rhubarb and sugar mixture.
Dot with oleo, add flour mixture on top and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: old fashioned cheese potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add the flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until a thick paste forms.
Gradually add milk, cook and stir until the mixture begins to thicken.
Add cheese, cook and stir until melted.
Place potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown chicken in skillet sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Stir in 1/2 cup salsa and 1 cup shredded cheese. Spread 1 cup salsa in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Place 1/4 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla and roll up. Place filled tortillas, seam side down, on top of salsa layer of baking dish. Top with remaining 1/2 cup of salsa and 1 cup shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut twinkies in half and place in bottom of 13 x 9 inch dish. Mix pudding mix, milk, condensed milk and Cool Whip. Pour on top of twinkies then pour on strawberries.

title: mixed greens with cornmeal dodgers
directions: Wash thoroughly the turnip greens, mustard greens and collard greens. Remove fibrous stems and tear leaves in heavy 8-quart pot. Place onion, ham, pepper, sugar, salt and Tabasco sauce in pot. Add enough cold water to cover greens completely. Bring to full boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat so liquid barely simmers. Cover and cook 2 hours.

title: peach muffins
directions: *Variation:
Substitute crushed, drained pineapple for peaches.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Blend butter, parsley, tarragon, chives, garlic, salt & pepper.
Shape into 4 inch square on aluminum foil & freeze for 30-40 minutes.
Pound chicken breasts to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut frozen butter into 12 pieces & place 1 piece in center of each chicken breast.
Fold chicken over butter making sure butter is sealed completely in chicken.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Roll chicken in flour, dip in eggs and then coat with bread crumbs and repeat coating process one more time.
Deep fry at 340° until deep golden brown.

title: jule kage(norwegian christmas bread)
directions: Mix yeast with lukewarm water in large mixing bowl.
(I use large Tupperware "cake taker" with lid to keep the dough warm.) Add milk, eggs and some flour and beat well.
Then add rest of ingredients and as much flour as needed to make soft, easy to handle dough.
Knead well and let rise until double, then knead again and let rise.
Put in 1 pound loaves or whatever you like (round cake pans, etc.) and rise until double.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes (watch).
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: lunch time favorite
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in casserole.
Add chow mein noodles over top when out of the oven and while hot.

title: holiday relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pizza bread
directions: Roll out bread dough and brown hamburger, sausage, onion and bell pepper until done.
Put 1/2 of your meat mixture on the end of your rolled out dough.
Spread meat out to the edges.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Fold dough over meat and cheese.
Pull dough as far as you can so that the other 1/2 ingredients can be laid on top and dough can be folded one more time.
Seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic butter.
Bake 7 minutes.
Slice.
Serve with sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop the stems. Simmer them for 2 minutes in 1 Tbsp. butter. Add to them: bread crumbs, almonds, chives and milk. Mix well. Season with salt and paprika. Brush the caps with butter. Place them cap side down on a greased broiler rack. Broil the mushrooms for 2 1/2 minutes. Reverse them. Place bread crumb mixture in each cap. Dot with butter. Broil them for 2 1/2 minutes longer. Serve them sizzling hot!

title: oven meal
directions: Place ingredients in baking dish in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process on low speed for 1 minute or until smooth.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Stir well before using.
Yields 2 cups.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy sauce pan over low heat; add flour stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk, cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: strawberry-nut shortcake
directions: Sweeten strawberries with 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside. Combine biscuit mix, 3 tablespoons sugar, 3 tablespoons butter, milk and nuts; mix until moistened.
Knead on floured board 4 to 5 times.
Roll or pat dough into circles, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut 8 (3-inch) circles, using biscuit cutter.
Place 4 circles on ungreased sheet; brush tops with melted butter.
Top with remaining circles.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Separate circles; fill with strawberries and topping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cooked pimento and cheese
directions: Melt American cheese and milk in a double boiler for 12 minutes.
Cook pimento, egg, vinegar and sugar for 30 minutes and while still warm add 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: bourbon chicken with peaches
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and arrange in 13 x 9-inch pan. Set aside. Melt butter in skillet over medium heat; add onion and saut 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in paprika. Add green onions, reserving 1 tablespoon. Cook, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes. Spread onion mixture over chicken. Drizzle with orange juice and bourbon. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes, turning occasionally and basting with pan drippings. Top with peaches and nutmeg. Bake 15 more minutes or until done. Sprinkle with reserved green onions.

title: mendy's pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt, flour and vanilla.
Fold in drained pineapple.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix undiluted soup, sugar, mustard, pepper, salad oil, vinegar, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil.
Let cool for a few minutes and pour over carrots and bell peppers.
Chill before serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, flour, salt and milk together.
Add the corn (liquid drained).
Melt the butter or margarine in the baking dish you are going to use.
Pour the mixture into the baking dish. Place the baking dish into a shallow pan filled with hot water to within 1-inch of the top of the baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk to the mixture (this will help to brown nicely). Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
(A cake tester should emerge clean.)
Good appetite!

title: peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and transparent.
Add peaches; cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with top crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is slightly brown.

title: super bean bowl
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place bean mixture into a deep round casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until meatballs are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: muffins in the mornin'
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup berries and stir in by hand.
Add rest of blueberries whole and stir in by hand. Grease muffin tins well with Crisco (top surface, too).
Pile the mix high in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle sugar over tops.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 30 minutes.

title: easy shortcake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Remove cake from pan and cool.
Wash pan and replace cooled cake.
Spread 2 cans pie filling over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over filling.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: portuguese sweet bread(a san jose specialty)
directions: In a small bowl, sprinkle yeast and pinch of sugar over warm water.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes; then stir to dissolve yeast; set aside for 5 to 6 minutes.
In a deep mixing bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, 4 cups flour and salt.
Make a well in center and pour in yeast, milk and 3 eggs.
Stir until mixed and beat until well mixed.
Beat in butter and add 2 cups of flour, 1/4 cup at a time, until dough can be made into a soft ball.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Blend flour, margarine and nuts.
Press on bottom of long baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheryl skymer's lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger.
Take skin off sausage; mince up and cook. Saute 4 garlic cloves in olive oil until almost done.
Add tomato sauce along with crushed tomatoes and a sprinkle of oregano.
Add in hamburger and sausage.
Drain off fat.
(Simmer for flavor.) Grate Mozzarella cheese in bowl.
Add large curd cottage cheese, 4 eggs, oregano, salt and pepper; mix together.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper.
Add the next 6 ingredients; simmer. Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauteed spinach
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Wash leaves and pat dry.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add green onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add spinach, sugar and salt.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until spinach is wilted and tender, stirring once.
Drain and serve immediately.
Yields 3 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cream shortening and sugar into dry mixture.
Add eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 10 minutes at 350°, then decrease heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: california egg salad
directions: Combine all except tomatoes and lettuce.
Cover and chill. To serve, cut tomatoes in 6ths almost to the edge.
Place them on beds of lettuce and put 3/4 cup heap of egg salad in center of the tomato flower.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into two greased loaf pans. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Let cool on wire rack.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Layer chicken breasts.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle cheese and stuffing.
Melt butter over.
Sprinkle seasoning on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine peaches and water; cook gently 10 minutes. Add sugar; slowly bring to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves. Cook rapidly until thick, about 15 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. Pour, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars. Adjust caps. Yield: About 4 pints.

title: ro-tel chicken
directions: Boil the chicken and debone. Grease bottom of long baking dish.
Put crushed Doritos on bottom, then layer of chicken.
Mix the soups, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Pour this over the chicken and layer again until all is used.
Over this, sprinkle the cheese and complete by making top layer with crushed Doritos.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low-fat garden pesto
directions: Add and process ingredients in the order listed.
Add water until desired consistency.
Adjust to taste and spread on sandwiches and pizza.
Add some liquid from cooking pasta and serve with pasta.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla, combine with raisins.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add chopped nut meats.
Blend well and chill.
Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain grease and crumble.
Mix sausage and Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle in pie shell.
In bowl, add remaining ingredients to lightly beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook & drain sausage.
Let hash browns thaw.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles & press in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press over bottom & sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage on rolls.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 min.

title: twinkle punch
directions: Add amount of water called for on orange juice and lemonade cans. Add cranberry juice, sugar and strawberries. Add ginger ale and sherbet ball last.

title: mama's chewy cookies
directions: Bake in square pan, greased, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Cut in squares.
Don't overcook.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Stir over medium heat to boiling. Boil for 3 minutes. Pour quickly into hot jars (6 ounce). Seal with paraffin or process 10 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Chill and serve.

title: bean and cheese wrap-ups
directions: Preheat
oven to 400°.	Combine all ingredients, except Pita bread,
and
mix
well.
Split
open one end of each Pita bread. Divide
filling
evenly
and
spoon into the open end. Wrap each sandwich tightly in a piece of aluminum foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie(diabetic)
directions: In medium bowl combine pumpkin, dry pudding mix, dry milk powder, pumpkin spice and water.
Mix well using a wire whisk. Blend in Cool Whip lite.
Pour mixture into pie crust. Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Spread remaining 3/4 Cool Whip on top of set filling, sprinkle pecans evenly on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops.
Slice potatoes and lay on top.
Mix the soups together and pour on top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In large glass bowl, layer bottom and sides with lettuce. Over lettuce layer separately in order: bell pepper, onions, cheese, celery, carrots and peas. Spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle sugar on top of mayo. Let set in refrigerator over night. Next day garnish with bacon and boiled eggs. Can also garnish with tomatoes and olives.

title: country baked steak
directions: Combine onion soup mix and water and set aside. Flour, salt and pepper steaks and brown quickly on both sides in small amount of oil. Place into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and pour soup mix over steaks. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until tender. Good served with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: crunchy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light; beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in uncooked oats and rest of ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies, 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute, then remove to cooling rack; store in tightly covered container.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook sausage and onion with oregano until done.
Stir to separate meat (use shortening, if necessary). Pour off fat.
Add soups and water.
Combine meat mixture and noodles.
Pour into 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch). Cover.
Bake for 40 minutes (375° to 400°) or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: cheese hominy
directions: Heat sour cream, Cheez Whiz and green chilies.
Pour over hominy and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well. Stir in oats and coconut. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pie tests done.

title: czechoslavakian cheese cake
directions: Combine flour, softened margarine and salt, cutting together like pie dough.
Set aside.
Combine yeast, warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir together.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add the egg. Stir a little.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Stir with a fork.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out one portion on floured surface into a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.

title: cold oven popovers
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flour and salt in the listed order in a blender.
Process on High for 1 minute.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Place in cold oven; turn oven to 450°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom.
In a bowl, mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into pan on top of coconut.
In separate bowl, put melted butter, softened cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix until smooth.
Pour on top of cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown Tater Tots as directed less 10 minutes. Brown and drain hamburger meat. Combine in 9 x 13 casserole dish partially cooked Tater Tots, browned hamburger and soup. Stir together and top with grated Cheddar. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until soup is hot and cheese is melted.

title: killer kake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Do not drain pineapple juice.
Flour and grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar to yeast and water. Add salt, oil and flour and mix well.
Grease bowl and put dough in and turn over so top of dough will be well-greased.
Put in warm place and let rise until doubled.
Roll out on floured paper and knead until stiff enough to make rolls.
Let rolls rise until doubled in size and bake at 425° until brown.

title: cranberry marshmallow salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, add marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip. Mix well together.
Serve cold.

title: cavatini
directions: Bring spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, onion and green pepper to a low boil.
Then mix noodles and hamburger.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green salad dressing
directions: Blenderize all ingredients together.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Cook, drain and rinse noodles.
Brown meat and onions.
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine milk, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and green pepper.
Heat to blend.
Alternate layers in casserole (2 quarts).
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 6 servings, 2 quarts.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add milk and pineapple (including juice or syrup).
Add 3 slices of the cubed bread, mixing gently.
Pour in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with remaining 2 slices of cubed bread.
Pour the melted butter on top and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon-butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan, over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and cornstarch.
Stir to blend.
Slowly add half and half, stirring constantly.
Add cornstarch and simmer until thickened.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups. For decoration:
gummy worms and frogs candy flowers, chopped nuts or granola.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Boil and stir 2 minutes until mixture reaches a hard boil that you can not stir down.
It will look light and foamy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix powdered sugar until smooth.
If it's hard to mix, use a mixer and add extra milk a teaspoon at a time.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: western potato rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.

Generously spray both sides of potato slice with oil. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown; remove from oven. Generously brush potato slices with barbecue sauce; sprinkle with cheese, onion and bacon.
Return potato slices to oven.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: martha otto's lemon squares
directions: Blend together flour, butter and confectioners sugar as for
a pie
crust.
Spread in an ungreased pan, 9 x 13-inches and
pack down into a crust; bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. While	crust is baking, beat the eggs with a fork and add the sugar,
salt, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Pour this mixture over the baked crust and return to oven for 25 minutes more.
Remove
from oven
and
dust with confectioners sugar. Cool and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: In a small saucepan, boil 1 cup water and add oats, honey, margarine and salt.
Let cool.
Combine yeast, sugar and 1/3 cup warm water in a large bowl or a food processor.
Let proof.
Add 2 cups flour to the yeast mixture.
When oat mixture is warm, but not hot, add it to the flour mixture and knead dough 10 minutes or process 15 seconds or until dough is smooth and elastic, adding more flour if necessary.

title: cinnamon rings
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into rings.
Soak rings in lime water for 24 hours.
Drain and wash in cool water.
Soak 3 hours in cool water.
Drain.

title: mud cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool completely.
Make pudding according to directions on box; cool completely.
In a large bowl, crumble 1/4 of cake.
Cover with 1/4 of pudding. Cover pudding with 1/4 Cool Whip.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Put in refrigerator to chill thoroughly.

title: 7 minute frosting - never fail
directions: Place all ingredients, except flavoring, in a bowl over boiling water or double boiler (bowl works best).
Beat for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring.
Frost cake.

title: creamed mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters. Place in a large stockpot with water to cover. Boil over high heat uncovered for 30 minutes or until soft. Drain and mash with potato masher or pass through a food mill. While hot, add butter, cream cheese, heavy cream and salt and pepper to taste. Whip until smooth with a wooden spoon.

title: millionaire pies
directions: Mix all
ingredients well and pour into 2 graham crusts. Refrigerate to set.
May top with additional Cool Whip.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in large pot, over medium heat, until browned.
Spoon off all but 2 teaspoons of drippings.
Add garlic and onions; cook until soft, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and their liquid, breaking up tomatoes with spoon.
Add broth, wine and basil.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add parsley, pepper, zucchini and pasta.
Simmer, stirring gently, for about 25 minutes or until pasta is al dente.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions; cool.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Chill.

title: sour cream hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8. Holds well in refrigerator.
This is a super quick dish.
Not expensive to make.
Great for any time or anywhere.

title: mushroom noodles
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water 15 minutes. Drain.
Put in buttered casserole and add soup that has been stirred smooth and mixed with water.
Mix together well and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: souper meat 'n potatoes pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes; top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more, or until done.
Garnish with cooked sliced bacon if desired.

title: best crock-pot meal ever
directions: Cook all ingredients, except pea pods, for 5 to 7 hours in crock-pot.

title: sliced baked potatoes(makes 4 servings.)
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped herbs.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese. Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes at High power until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve potatoes as a side dish or as a main dish with just a salad.

title: pralines
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except vanilla, in a 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Continue stirring to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes. Add vanilla; beat with wooden spoon until candy begins to thicken. Drop rapidly from tablespoon onto waxed paper.
(If candy becomes too stiff to drop, stir in 1/2 tablespoon hot water.)
Makes 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt margarine in soup kettle.
Add chopped onion; cook until limp, not brown.
Add ground beef; stir and cook until red color is gone.
Pour in tomatoes, consomme and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover kettle; cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Great main course, Gene's favorite.

title: easy beef cubes with gravy
directions: Place beef cubes in a baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom and onion soup.
Stir, cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over egg noodles or rice. Serves 4 to 5.

title: overnight chicken dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mince pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add vegetables and gravy.
Mix. Put mixture in one pie crust.
Use second crust as lid.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: italian sausage pie
directions: Place bottom pie crust into 9-inch pie plate.
Lightly scramble 3 eggs.
Cut sausage into cubes and cut Mozzarella cheese into cubes.
Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Take the remaining top pie crust and cut into strips.
Lay strips crisscross on top of pie and use a fork to press ends of crust together.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 70 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread on tray; top with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: captain amigo's chili
directions: To make sauce, put all dry ingredients, herbs, water, canned tomatoes, paste and sauce in big pot on medium heat.
In frying pan, saute garlic and 1/2 onions in bacon fat.
Add meat, cut in 1-inch cubes and sausage.
Add to pot of sauce.
In same pan, brown ground beef with other 1/2 of the onions.
Add to sauce pot. Reduce heat to a simmer and cook until all ingredients have a chance to meld.
Serves a crowd.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, peppers and onion; drain.
In a pan, put tortillas and some shredded cheese.
Then a layer of meat mixture. Then more tortillas and more shredded cheese, then more meat mixture.
Then put in oven for 30 minutes then more cheese until cheese is hot.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut up round steak, beef strips or beef cubes into bite size pieces.
Deer meat is good also.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add butter, chicken bouillon and garlic.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Boil 10 more minutes.

title: chip chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, toss chicken, celery, green pepper, onion and mayonnaise; cover and chill.
Just before serving, mix in potato chips.
Serve on salad or lettuce leaves.
Garnish with melon wedges and strawberries.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine water, yeast and sugar.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Stir in crushed Vitamin C, 1/2 flour, oil and salt.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Add flour until it can't be stirred, then knead by hand until remainder of flour is used up.
Knead until dough has the consistency of bubble gum.
Let rise until doubled; punch down.
Form into 2 or 3 loaves.
Place into greased loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: cinnamon bread shapes
directions: In shallow bowl, combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon. Separate the bread sticks and dip in pecan mixture.
Shape as desired.
Place on baking sheet lightly coated with cooking spray. Bake at 375 for 13-15 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve warm.

title: an "old time" lemon taffy
directions: Put all ingredients at once in a pan and cook to a hard-ball stage, tested in ice cold water.
When cooked sufficiently, add 1 teaspoon lemon extract.
Stir just enough to blend in.
Immediately pour on buttered plates to cool.
This needs no stretching, but it should be very hard and brittle.
This is very good.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: favorite scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Beat buttermilk and egg in small bowl.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir with fork until mixture comes together.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough 5 or 6 times.
Transfer to greased cookie sheet.
Pat into 8-inch circle and cut into 8 wedges or cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in a 425° oven for 14 to 16 minutes.

title: gratin dauphinois(dauphine-style potato gratin)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190° C).
Peel the garlic and crush in a garlic press into a large saucepan.
Add the milk and cream and bring to boil over low heat.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg. Meanwhile, peel the potatoes, wash them and pat dry.
Using the shredder attachment of a food processor, slice them very thinly. Butter a 10 x 7-inch baking dish.
Add the potatoes and pour the mixture on them.
Smooth the surface with a wooden spoon.
Bake until golden brown, about 50 minutes.
Serve hot from the baking dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix
eggs,
milk,
vanilla and sugar; add flour and mix thoroughly.
Now,
add sweet potatoes; pour in pan or bowl and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bacon and mushroom quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Measure ingredients. Crumble bacon into 1/2-inch chunks.
Lower oven rack and preheat oven to 350°.

title: marinated summer sunset salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, tossing gently.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add lettuce and pine nuts, tossing gently to coat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.	Blend in mashed sweet potatoes
and
milk.
In
separate	bowl
mix
in flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.	Add dry ingredients and raisins
to egg mixture.
Stir only until just mixed.
Put into muffin
pans.
Bake
in
oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Slice strawberries; mix with glaze.
Mix pudding by directions on box.
Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Put layer of cake, layer of pudding mixture and layer of strawberry mixture, then layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat until all is used.
Top layer should be Cool Whip.
Large glass bowl recommended.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in three greased and floured pans.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it will spin a thread.
Pour half of it into 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook other half until it will harden in water.
Pour in other half.
Beat until creamy; pour into buttered dish or drop from spoon.
You may add chopped nuts or coconut as desired but not until it has cooled quite a bit.
If too hot, it will draw out the oil and it will not harden.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into pan with heated oil.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: blackberry crumble
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until thick.
It may be necessary to break fresh berries to produce juice.
Set aside this filling mixture.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Blend and beat at low speed 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until light.
Add vanilla. Add flour and mix well.
Fold in walnuts.
Shape into small balls (walnut size).
Bake at 350° until bottoms are lightly browned. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Use 1/2 at a time.
Make 2 layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
corn chips, chicken, broth, pepper, onion and cheese.
Repeat.
Mix the chicken soup, garlic salt and chili powder.
Pour over layers; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except chicken, corn chips and cheese. In casserole, make 2 layers, starting with chips and ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sundae cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Use finger to punch holes in cake, about an inch apart.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over cake.
Pour sundae topping over cake.
Put 8 ounces of Cool Whip on next and sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top.
Store in fridge.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix sour cream and soda.
Add enough flour to make dough firm but not stiff.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Roll out on a well floured area and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for only 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges.
Don't overbake. Frost and decorate.

title: mixed peas and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
In a pot, combine peas and rice.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash and cook eight medium-size potatoes with jackets on. Peel potatoes and cube them.
Combine chopped hard-boiled eggs, salt, celery seed, celery, onions, pickles, mustard, mayonnaise and Miracle Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: fresh broccoli and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain and set aside.

title: bobbie's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except crabmeat and sherry in top of double boiler, then add crabmeat and sherry.
Keep warm.
Serve with king size Fritos.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix and bake 50 to 55 minutes in 325°.

title: chocolate chip and peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine peanut butter and butter, mix until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla, beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt; stir in 1 cup milk chocolate morsels. spread into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels; let sit 5 minutes until morsels are soft.
Spread chocolate evenly over top. Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa and flour; add sugar, salt, milk and oleo.
Heat. When warm, add a little to egg yolks.
Add yolks to cocoa mixture; cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool, pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff, add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie.
Brown in oven.

title: macaroni medley("carry-along dish")
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water (see package directions); drain.
Saute onion and green pepper until soft, not brown.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add salt, tomato sauce and water to beef mixture.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix olives and cheese with macaroni but keep 1 cup cheese for topping.
Place half of macaroni mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; cover with half of the meat mixture.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle on the 1 cup cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Sift together salt, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, butter and melted chocolate.
Place in an 8-inch square pan and sprinkle on sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over batter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Will be frosted when baked.

title: grandpa's spinach dip
directions: Cook, drain and cool spinach.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and soup.
Chop onions and chestnuts and add to mayonnaise mixture. Squeeze water out of spinach and chop.
Add spinach to mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut off top of French bread; scoop out bread and put dip in crust.
Serve with bread crusts.

title: festive eggnog
directions: Combine 1 quart of milk with the flour and sugar in a large saucepan.
Over medium heat, stir until the mixture boils. Continue to cook for 2 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil water and stir in rice and salt. Cover and simmer until the water is gone (approximately 30 minutes).
Add milk; boil gently, stirring occasionally until the mix thickens slightly (approximately 5 minutes).
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Gradually stir in rice mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
If desired, stir in raisins and sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon over top.
Place casserole dish in a pan containing approximately 1 inch of hot water and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until right consistency to spread on cake.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
May garnish with bacon bits, if desired.

title: hazelnut cake with chocolate frosting
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored; beat in sugar and then the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a spring-form pan. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine evaporated milk, soup and seasoned salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add vegetables, chicken, rice and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and the croutons.
Bake for additional 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix rice, corn and beef.
Press in casserole dish; cover with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: classic american pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut or rub in half of the butter or shortening, then the other half.
Sprinkle the ice water, one tablespoon at a time, over mixture.
With fork, toss mixture together.
Continue until the dough is just moist enough to hold together when pressed.
Gather into a ball, wrap in plastic wrap, and chill for at least one hour.
Take dough from the refrigerator and roll out on a lightly floured surface until it is about 1/8 inch thick and about 2 inches larger in diameter than your pie plate.
This gives you enough to make a good high rim for a single crust shell.
Keep dough chilled until ready to use.
The dough can be chilled for up to a month or frozen until needed.

title: lazy green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans; drain.
Add soup and onion.
Place in buttered Pyrex pan and top with can of onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange slice cake
directions: In small mixing bowl cream soda and butter, then add to sugar. Next add one egg at a time.
Next add buttermilk.
Put flour
in large bowl.
Add fruit to flour.
Then add cream mix to
flour. Mix
well by hand.
Bake in oven at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: white sweet potato meringue pie
directions: Bake or boil potatoes; peel while hot.
Mix in a large bowl 2 cups mashed potatoes, egg yolks, butter, sugar, flour, milk and flavoring.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place crumbs in baking pan (1 1/2-quart).
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add all other ingredients, stirring well.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° until a toothpick comes out clean.
Glaze if desired.

title: polish teacakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolk; mix well. Add flour and salt; mix.
Roll dough in small balls; dip in unbeaten egg white.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on buttered baking sheet; press down center of each with thimble. Bake in a 325° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove; press down again with thimble.
Return to oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; fill indents with preserves while hot.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Put beef, onion and bacon in a food processor.
Process until mixed well.
With your hands, mix in bread crumbs, egg and salt. Form into bite size balls.
Brown in frying pan.
Lower heat and cook a few minutes.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Place all ingredients except pasta into a Dutch oven.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add more water as needed.
Stir in pasta.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: janice's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Stir until melted. Pour in buttered oblong pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: pork chops - ed's style
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides; mix two cans together (broth and cream of chicken soup).
Pour over chops.
Simmer 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or grits with hot biscuits.
Good.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of crushed potato chips.
Pour in chicken mixture and cover top with remaining crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix well.
Make into patties.
Fry in hot Crisco oil until golden brown on both sides and drain on paper towels.
Delicious cold or leftover.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and chocolate syrup; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add pineapple juice. Freeze in plastic containers.
Set out about an hour before wanting to use.
Stir it up and pour 4 bottles ginger ale over it. Serves 50.

title: baked peach pancake
directions: In a bowl, combine peaches with sugar and lemon juice; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, milk and salt; beat until smooth.
Place butter in a 10-inch skillet; bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until melted.
Immediately pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until pancake has risen and is puffed all over.
Fill with peach slices and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve immediately with sour cream, if desired.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy beef and noodles stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet or electric skillet, saute beef and onion. Add wine, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, beef broth, water, seasonings and noodles.
Cover.
Heat to boiling.
Lower heat and cook until noodles are done, 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir in yogurt or sour cream and heat through.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: macaroni-cheese-tuna casserole
directions: In greased 2-quart baking dish, combine macaroni, butter, cheese, salt, pepper, peas and tuna.
Combine eggs, milk and soup. Pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown on top.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: beans and macaroni
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, saute garlic in oil until cooked. Do not let it burn. Add celery, carrots, pepperoni, oregano, red pepper, black pepper and tomato paste. Add water to cover vegetables. Cover and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat powdered sugar and cream until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on crumbs.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill.
This is yummy.

title: date scones
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Rub in butter until mixture resembles fine bread crumbs.
Stir in dates and sugar.
Beat egg and add to dry ingredients with sufficient milk to give soft dough.
Place on floured surface and knead lightly.
Pat out to approximately 1 cm. (1/2-inch) using a 5 cm. (2-inch) floured cutter, cut into rounds. Place onto lightly greased over tray.
Glaze tops with milk. Bake in a very hot oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 scones.

title: sweet yeast rolls
directions: Combine Jiffy cake mix, dry yeast and salt, then gradually add water.
Stir until blended.
Stir in flour.
Cover with a towel and let rise until double in bulk in a warm place.
Roll on floured board to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Dip in butter and fold in half.
Place in greased pan and let rise until double. Bake in 350° oven until brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat egg; add milk.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt. Throw together.
Drop by spoonfuls into stew or roast.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, without peeking!

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill. Very good served with angel food or pound cake.

title: chocolate nut torte(passover)
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix yolks with sugar in separate bowl and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add enough water to cocoa to make a thick paste.
Add to yolk mixture and blend.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 10-inch spring-form pan 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into chunks.
Place in processor or blender and chop medium fine.
Put in strainer and press out as much liquid as possible.
(This is important or spread will be watery.)
Mix vegetables, salt, mayonnaise and cream cheese. Refrigerate overnight or several days.
Serve on breads of your choice.
Cut into shapes or use as a dip.
Sandwiches can be made day before; put into container and refrigerate.

title: old fashion raisin cookies
directions: Add enough flour to roll out and cut.
Chill dough.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese and tomato tart(feuillete de chevre)
directions: Puff pastry comes in sheets folded in thirds. Two-thirds will fit in a lasagna pan or use a large cookie sheet for the whole sheet.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown beef and drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet mustard sauce fish
directions: Roll fish in cornmeal or potato chips.
Place fish in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or grill.
Bake uncovered at 450° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together everything except peaches.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine in casserole.
Pour mixture into melted butter.
Add peaches; stir lightly.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and Crisco.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order listed in salad bowl. Spread mayonnaise evenly over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Chill covered for 4 hours or longer.
Top with bacon before serving.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix
cheese,
onions,
mayonnaise
and pepper together. Form with
hands to make ring (like jello ring) with a hole in the center.
Fill
hole, just before serving, with strawberry preserves.
Put
pecans
on
outer
edge
of cheese ring, then refrigerate to firm up.
Best if served with wheat crackers.

title: chocolate marshmallow crisps
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Place beans in bottom of dish (9 x 10-inch is good size).
Add corn evenly over beans.
Mix soup, onions, sour cream, cheese and garlic salt.
Pour over corn.
Mix crushed crackers with nuts and oleo; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Strain and set aside broth.
Remove meat from bones and layer in a casserole dish.
You can dice some onion and celery over chicken.
Spread both cans of soup over this.
Mix dressing in broth and pour on top.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: the neiman marcus cookie
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend oats to a fine powder. Cream the butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts if desired.
Form into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly into 2-quart bowl; stir in sugar, salt, vanilla, syrup and butter.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Place on bottom rack in middle of the oven and cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (do not overcook).
Filling will be slightly soft looking when gently shaken.
Serve with whipping cream on top or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: fluffy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese; beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shell and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: tasty chuck roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan or Corning Ware with a tight lid. May use meat with or without bone (any meat with bone in is more tasty).
Sprinkle all seasonings on top.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cook 5 to 6 hours at 300°.
Do not add water.
Makes its own juices.

title: almond butter balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flavorings and stir in flour and nuts.
Blend well.
Form dough into tiny balls and
place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While still warm, roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Cover potatoes, carrots, celery and onions with water. Cook until tender. Add the milk, bouillon cubes and cheese. Cook until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: ken's marinade for deer meat
directions: Dissolve in cup water and bouillon cubes in microwave.
Place all ingredients in a Ziploc bag with meat.
Take air out of bag. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets and rinse well.
Cook to crisp-tender stage; do not overcook.
Drain and add celery, shallots and thawed peas.

title: cookie bars
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir to cool slightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fill large saucepan with 4 quarts water.
Add potatoes, onion and celery.
Let boil until vegetables are tender.
Add salt to taste, the margarine and clams.
Add the cornstarch to the boiling mixture.
Let boil again.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Put egg whites in a small bowl and roll each ball into egg whites.
Roll into nuts.
Put on cookie sheet.
Make thumbprints in each ball before baking.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Put icing, jelly or chocolate kiss in center to decorate.

title: sweet-and-sour corn relish
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Add red and green peppers, onion, sugar, cayenne pepper and salt.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in corn and vinegar; heat through.
Refrigerate to serve cold later.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix and bring to boil; boil 5 minutes.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour macaroni into melted butter; stir until coated.
Add salt, pepper, cubed cheese and cold milk. Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while baking. This comes out of oven golden brown and creamy.
Excellent with cubed ham baked in also!

title: dark lady salad
directions: Congeal.
Add one small container Cool Whip.
Nuts are good, too.

title: excellent dressing for salads or slaws
directions: Mix ingredients together. Shake well.
Tastes great on tomato salad, green salad, or cabbage.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix well and cook at 350° for 30 minutes in greased sheet pan.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound cutlets thin.
Coat with flour so that as much flour as possible adheres to both sides of the cutlets.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Place cutlets into the skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Saute quickly until golden brown over medium high heat.
Remove as soon as both sides are done.
If necessary, remove first group of cutlets and do second group.
When all cutlets are sauteed, place all cutlets in pan and add Marsala. Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove slices to a hot platter.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Combine dates, water and soda.
Set aside until cool.
Combine eggs, butter and sugar.
Add cooled date mixture and stir well. Add flour, cocoa, soda, powder, vanilla and salt.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix chips, nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle on top of batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all but chocolate chips.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Fold in 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into greased tube pan and top with remaining chips.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Cook pasta and have ready to serve. Melt butter and sauteed onions. Add blackened spice, shrimp and tomatoes. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring twice. Cut cream cheese into 4 pieces and add to shrimp mixture. Add crab and mushrooms NOW. Cover for 1 minute and then stir until cheese is smooth. Add sour cream and continue to stir. Serve over pasta. Enjoy!!!

title: chicken and rice supreme
directions: Cook rice using package directions.
Combine with green beans, chicken, pimentos, water chestnuts, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° to 350° until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Half-cook broccoli and put in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart square casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over broccoli. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cracker crumbs and grated sharp cheese may be put over top of mixture before baking.

title: coconut-pecan frosting for german chocolate cake
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Only frost tops of cake layers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream lard and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add finely chopped dates or nuts and blend well.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk; mix well.
Drop one at a time from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain.
Heat in oven to melt cheese chunks and serve warm.
I usually put in a crock-pot after it is all melted.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Layer cabbage, diced peppers, onions and pimentos.
Make two or three layers.
Use the sliced peppers and onions and rest of pimentos by arranging them on the top.
Do not stir.
Bring to boil sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Boil 2 minutes; pour over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Let it set for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Can be kept up to a week in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: tropical cake
directions: Bake white cake in 14 x 9-inch pan as directed on box.
Cool. Poke holes in cake approximately every 2 inches.
I use the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour can of crushed pineapple including juice over the top and into the holes.
Recipe calls for a small can but I have use the larger can.
Mix large box instant vanilla pudding.
I use sugar-free.
Cover cake and crushed pineapple with pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: raspberry and pineapple salad
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Stir in partially thawed raspberries and crushed pineapple.
Whip cream; blend into mixture.
Pour into individual molds.
Set in fridge.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix in enough flour to make a dough-like non-sticky cookie dough.
Divide into 5 or 6 balls. Pat into 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: savory chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Top with Swiss cheese slices.

title: tejas relish
directions: Dice tomatoes (not too fine) and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside while preparing other ingredients.
Squeeze the tomatoes out of the salty juice and throw away the juice.
Mix tomatoes with the diced onions and pepper.
I usually use 2 peppers and taste. Then add peppers until hot enough.
Pour vinegar over sugar and bring almost to a boil.
Mix all other ingredients in electric roaster and set at 300° for about 10 minutes.
Pour hot vinegar and sugar over tomato mixture.
Reduce heat to 200° and simmer for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Never let it boil and don't overcook.
Taste until it seems done.
Bottle and seal.
Makes approximately 12 pints.

title: graham cracker eclairs
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers, then a layer of pudding and top with more whole graham crackers.
Cover with chocolate frosting from can.
Refrigerate.
Make night before.

title: walnut bread
directions: Mix sugar, Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Beat hard for 30 seconds. Add 1 1/2 cups chopped walnuts.
Pour into a buttered loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato cakes
directions: In a large bowl, stir together mashed potatoes, egg, onion and flour.
After mixing is completed, heat oil in a large heavy skillet. When oil is hot, drop potato mixture into hot oil. Brown well, using medium heat.
Turn and brown well.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix Rice Krispies with peanut butter and honey. Press into the bottom of a pie pan (sprayed with Pam). Place sliced banana over crust. Pour pudding over bananas. Top with Cool Whip. Entire recipe is about 20 points.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mash bananas, through a sieve.
(Usually takes 3 bananas to make 1 cup.)
Add bananas to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and soda together, twice.
Add to banana mixture, stirring lightly.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barb's punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.

title: herb roasted potatoes poupon
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes in small bowl.
Place potatoes in lightly greased 13 x 9 baking pan or cookie sheet. Toss with mustard mixture.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil the first three ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Use electric coffeepot or percolator to keep hot while serving, or put in pot on stove.

title: casserole of butter beans
directions: Cook and stir onion, sugar and garlic in drippings until bubbly and caramel looking.
Add beans and bacon; place into casserole in a low temperature oven, 325°, and bake 1 1/2 hours. (May need to add a tablespoon or two of water.)

title: stew beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large Dutch oven.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter; mix with hands until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of mixture to be used later.
Place remainder of mixture in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly along bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: baked potatoes with cheese
directions: Rub potatoes with bacon fat and season with salt.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 375°, turning occasionally.
Cut off tops of potatoes while hot and scoop out all of potatoes from inside. Using a press-type sieve, sieve the cooked potato into bowl.
(You need 2 cups potato puree.)

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Soak bran in hot water.
Cream sugar with butter.
Add eggs; beat well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Add raisins as preferred.
Spoon into muffin tin.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Keeps well in refrigerator for approximately 6 weeks.
Use as desired.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen muffins.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and sugar together.
Grease angel food cake pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pudding mixture.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls, then add nuts.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake in a casserole dish 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: shrimp wiggle
directions: Melt over low heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour.
Blend well.
Add gradually 1 cup milk.
Cook until smooth. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup cooked (or canned) shrimp and 1/2 cup cooked peas.
Keep hot over boiling water on very low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: spicy chicken pizza
directions: Saut onion, green pepper and celery in a skillet sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Stir in sauce from package, chicken and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes and remove from heat. Prepare crust mix according to directions.
Spray Pam on a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish and spread dough out.
Evenly spread chicken mixture over the dough and sprinkle with the grated cheese from the package.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Rinse berries; cut orange and apples into wedges.
Put all in food chopper (it will be juicy so place bowl under chopper to catch and use juices).
Stir in sugar several times.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook together ground chuck, onion and garlic; drain fat. Add tomatoes, sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and basil. Heat to boiling. Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cream sweet potatoes, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add cinnamon, biscuit mix and form into ball.
More biscuit mix may be needed if sticky.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy pan.
Add onion, 2 cloves garlic, carrots and celery.
Saute vegetables until onion is transparent. Add potatoes, tomatoes, zucchini, green beans, black pepper and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add white beans and pasta.
Add more water if soup is too thick.
In blender, blend basil, 1 clove of garlic and 1 cup of soup from the pot.
Return this mixture to the soup; mix in and serve.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: About 2 1/2 quarts.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: butterscotch chipper bars
directions: Stir together oats, flour, sugar, butterscotch chips, salt and soda.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pat into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Then add apple and nuts.
Batter will be very stiff.
Pat into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Mix granulated sugar, nuts, butter or margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside.
Cream together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Thoroughly stir together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in rhubarb. Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cool.
