title: italian dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chittlings
directions: Clean
chittlings, removing all fat and dirt.
In large pot, put clean chittlings.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Leave enough liquid so	that
chittlings are just covered.
Add seasonings and cook for about 4 hours on low fire.
Serve with cornbread, pickled peppers, greens of your choice and candied yams.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and light syrup in 3 quart saucepan over moderate heat until mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Mix in Rice Krispies. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; let harden. Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate and butterscotch morsels; stir until blended. Spread over Krispies mixture. Chill about 5 minutes until top is firm. Cut into bars. (Can use 1 large package chocolate morsels and 1/2 package butterscotch morsels.)

title: ruth's meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together and spoon out 1 tablespoon at a time. Roll in hand to form a meatball.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in four pieces.
Shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits in greased tube pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts between layers, if desired.
Melt brown sugar with margarine and boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: lemonade(fresh)
directions: Combine water and lemon juice.
Add apple juice to sweeten. You may add more apple juice if your taste runs sweeter. Refrigerate.
Serve with a sprig of mint in each glass.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Coat chicken with flour and brown in oil.
Place the browned chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix catsup and cola and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: rolled jalapeno pinwheels
directions: * When handling Jalapeno peppers, wear something like medical gloves or even sandwich bags on your hands to protect from burning.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and flour.
Beat eggs; add milk, lemon juice, lemon rind and melted butter.
Add dry ingredients and blend well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cover rice with water and boil until water is gone.
Add milk, sugar, salt and butter and simmer until rice is cooked.
Beat eggs along with 1 tablespoon milk and cornstarch, then stir a little of the hot mixture into them.
Add slowly to keep eggs from curdling. Pour egg mixture into milk and rice.
Stir until well blended. Add vanilla.
Pour into serving dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon. Can be served hot.

title: aunt otry's chicken pot pie
directions: Spread chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Put vegetables over chicken.
Melt butter and mix all other ingredients in separate dish. Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° to 375°.
Check at 1 hour to see if browned.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds (by hand with spoon).
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still warm, brush biscuits with a mixture of the garlic powder and melted oleo.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: almond bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons powdered sugar over top, if desired and bake for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Bake squash in hot oven (400°) about 35 minutes or until tender.
Cut into half lengthwise and scoop out center, leaving shells about 1/4-inch thick.
Mash pulp and combine with remaining ingredients.
Pile mixture into squash shells and place in moderate (350°) oven to brown.
Allow 1 squash for 2 servings.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix and shape into balls.
Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and place Hershey's Kiss on cookie.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes more.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: kraut-noodle-sausage casserole
directions: In a casserole, put a layer of kraut, layer of uncooked noodles and layer of smoked sausage, ending with layer of kraut. Cover with water and bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: apple topped pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet, transfer to baking pan.
Season.
Core and slice unpeeled apples to 1/2-inch rings.
Add butter to skillet in which chops were browned and saute apple rings until tender.
Place one ring on each chop.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle honey over apples and chops.
Baste with drippings.
Cover and bake another 15 minutes or until done. Place cherry in center of apple rings before serving.
Serves 6.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain and mix vegetables together. Mix sugar and vinegar. Heat slightly to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining oil and spices. Mix dressing with vegetables and refrigerate for at least 2-3 hours before serving.

title: hearty hungarian goulash
directions: In a Dutch oven or a large saucepan, heat oil and brown the beef.
Add Lipton soup mix and paprika, blended with tomatoes. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.

title: amadama bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cornmeal, Crisco, molasses and salt.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over mixture; let cool.
Put 2 packages yeast in 1/2 cup warm water to dissolve.
Pour over mixture and add flour until dough forms a ball.
Knead for 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, double in size, punch down and rise 1 more hour.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peach brandy slush
directions: Steep together for 15 minutes first two ingredients.
Stir 7 cups of water and sugar together until sugar is dissolved.
Add tea, juices and brandy; mix well.

title: turkey chop suey
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender, but not brown. Add turkey, broth, celery and water chestnuts.
Heat to boiling.
Combine water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir into turkey mixture. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add bean sprouts and heat through. Serve on hot rice.
Sprinkle with roasted almonds.
If desired, pass additional soy sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meatball casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix first four ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Shape into balls and brown on all sides in hot margarine.
Put in 3 quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, including salt.
Arrange on top of meatballs.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven.
Bake 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: "sweet-sour meatballs"(makes 6 servings - 1978)
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, dissolve 2 teaspoons bouillon in water.
In large bowl, combine beef, crumbs, onion, bouillon liquid and egg; mix well.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
In large skillet, brown meatballs; pour off fat.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put all ingredients together and chill.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix and add corn and deboned chicken.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Slit chiles lengthwise.
Rinse and remove seeds, drain.
Insert strips of cheese in chiles and place in bottom of pan.
Heat water, milk and garlic salt to boiling in 2-quart pan and remove from heat. Stir in potatoes just until moistened.
Let stand until liquid is absorbed 30 seconds.
Whip with a fork until smooth, cool slightly.
Beat potatoes, eggs and baking powder until blended and light.
Pour over chiles.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean.
Last 15 minutes, pour salsa on top and continue to bake.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl combine corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Add the margarine, yogurt, eggs and cheese.
Stir until blended.
Heat oil in a large cast-iron skillet over medium heat.
Pour the hot oil into corn meal mixture.
Stir until combined.
Pour mixture into skillet.
Bake 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.
(Each serving is 204 calories.)

title: corn delight
directions: Stir all the ingredients into a two-quart greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour covered, plus 1/2 hour uncovered. Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingreidents together. Add eggs one at a time. Mix in melted butter and oil. Mix and add vanilla. Chill well. Roll size of walnuts and mash down with a glass dipped in sugar. May decorate with colored sugar. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil together syrup and sugar, then add eggs, salt, vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then 300° for 15 minutes.

title: fluffy biscuits
directions: Cut
flour
into
Crisco.
Blend well.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Roll dough on floured surface or board;
roll about 1-inch thick.
Cut
with
biscuit
cutter.
Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Put beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and butter in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Dip in corn flake crumbs.
Heat oil in frypan and brown on both sides. Turn down heat.
Cover pan and simmer for 15 minutes longer.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Put all together in pan.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes. Stir frequently.
Let cool and add 2 tablespoons baking soda in 2 tablespoons water and 2 cups flour.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: p l t's
directions: Provolone cheese can be pan-fired or browned in a microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, drained and cut into strips or crumbled for this modification of a standard.
While not fat-free, it is lower in fat than bacon and is a good substitute for vegetarian diets.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients.
Add the basil, oregano and parsley to the sauteed mixture.
Next, add the cheese and the beaten eggs to the mixture.
Line a 9 x 10-inch pan with the crescent roll.
Bring the crescent roll around the sides of the pan.
Pour the mixture into the pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: Mix all together.

Cover and store in refrigerator for 24 hours. Make into four loaves. Wrap in aluminum foil, leaving ends open. Poke holes in bottom of foil. Place loaves on cookie sheet. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°. Slice thin.
Serve with crackers. Keep in refrigerator.
Keeps 4 to 6 weeks.

title: chicken fricassee with dumplings
directions: Dumplings:
Follow directions on side of Bisquick box with the exception of adding approximately 1 teaspoon parsley flakes to the Bisquick prior to adding the milk.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients (shortening and 2 sugars).
Add eggs and vanilla and cream together.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook sausage and onion in 3-quart saucepan until sausage is light brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, beans, broth, water, zucchini and basil.
Break up tomato with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until zucchini is tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese when served.

title: winchester nut bread
directions: Put in a bowl brown sugar and cold water.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Add molasses and milk.
Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to the dry ingredients whole wheat flour.
Combine the mixtures.
Stir in walnut meats in large pieces.
Spoon into two buttered pans, 9 x 5-inches.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs and butter; pat firmly on bottom of 9 inch pan. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add condensed milk, beat until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Fold in chocolate chips; pour into pan. Bake for about 1 hour. Cool to room temperature. Chill.

title: english muffin canapes
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on muffins.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Cut into quarters to serve.
These can also be frozen, then put under broiler without defrosting.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil together the fruits, water, and oleo.
Mix together eggs, soda, salt, flour, vanilla, and nuts.
Add batter to fruit mixture.
Bake in 7x11 pan at 350 degrees for 15 minutes, if you want spicy bars add 1/2 tsp cinnamon and 1/4 tsp nutmeg.

title: rye bread
directions: Scald milk.
Put in mixing bowl the sugar, shortening and salt. Add scalded milk; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Stir until softened.
Add to lukewarm mixture.
Add six cups sifted flour.
Mix until smooth.
Sprinkle caraway seed on dough and add rye flour.
Knead until elastic on rye floured board. Place in greased bowl.
Brush top of dough with salad oil.
Put in warm place to rise double.
Knead again on rye board.
Shape into 2 large or 4 small loaves and place in well-greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until double and bake at 350° for 30 minutes for small or 45 minutes for large.
Turn out and brush with butter and let cool on wire rack.

title: almond, apricot, allspice cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients listed.
Cream together the butter or oleo and sugar. Add eggs and wheat germ. Beat thoroughly. Add dry ingredients alternately with the jar of baby food.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into ball. Refrigerate for several hours. Roll ball in 1/2 cup pecans and parsley (using the other 1/2 cup pecans in the ball).

title: kahlua mousse cake* * * * *
directions: This is another entree that is time consuming.
The first time I tried it, it took 3 hours to make 16, but don't be discouraged; with practice, it takes less time.
You'll receive rave reviews! These may also be frozen before baking.
You could also use butter flavored cooking spray instead of the butter on the phyllo leaves.

title: cheddar beer dip
directions: Mix together everything (except parsley).
Chill.
At serving time, garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers, etc.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: seafood dip
directions: Drain seafood and mix with cocktail sauce and horseradish. Pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, add 2 cups water, brown gravy mix and 2 beef bouillon cubes. Add meat loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in oven.
Serves 8.

title: shirley fey's chocolate sensation quick cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed blend all ingredients for
seconds.
Beat
at medium speed for 2 minutes or 300
strokes by hand.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back
when touched lightly in
center.
Cool
for
10 minutes. Frost as desired.
Enjoy.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all of ingredients together and make into balls.
Place into deep baking dish.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in large bean pot or casserole 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 24.

title: swedish egg pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour batter 1/3 cup at a time into heated pan.
After bubbles form, turn.
Serve with maple syrup or berries.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Parboil beans until tender.
Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Stir flour into beef.
Pour tomatoes into beef and break up tomatoes into bite size chunks.
Place all ingredients in large crock-pot, including most of liquid from beans.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: poor man muffins
directions: Place sugar, margarine, raisins, water and spices in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Put in paper lined muffin cups and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 15.

title: microwave hamburger quiche
directions: Crumble beef into 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave at High 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until meat loses its pink color.
Break up and drain. In medium bowl combine remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into pie plate.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave 4 minutes.
Push cooked portions to center of plate.
Microwave 4 1/2 to 8 minutes or until almost set, lifting edges of set egg after half the cooking time.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave 1 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand several minutes before serving.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Cream the shortening and sugar until very light. Add flour mixture alternating with milk and beat until smooth and light.
Add vanilla and egg whites beaten very stiff; fold in well.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Cover
dried
apples with water (about 2 cups) and soak overnight.	Chop
fine.
Add
molasses
and
simmer
hours. Cool.
Mix	sugar
and oleo; add eggs and blend well.
Mix dry ingredients to sugar, oleo and egg mix along with cooled dried apple-molasses
mixture.
Add sour milk.
Bake in greased loaf pans.
This
is a large amount so it makes 2 to 3 large loaves or 6
to
tiny foil tins.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour and 10 minutes,
for
tiny
loaves
or
1 1/2 hours for large loaves. Chopped
raisins
can be added to the apple-molasses mix.
Add before simmering.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt in saucepan. Drop in spices and simmer 5 minutes. Place eggs in jar or bowl. Cover with vinegar solution and add cloves. Let cool, then cover and place in refrigerator for 2 days to marinate.

title: ambrosia refrigerator cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in pineapple and oranges. Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix 1 cup coconut.
Whip cream with remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.
Fold into jello mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Chill until firm.
Toast remaining coconut and use as a garnish before serving.
Serves 16.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in a 1/2-quart microwavable dish.
Put in microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Stir peanuts into sugar mixture and microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir in soda and pour into pan. Cool for approximately 1 hour.

title: cake won't last
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Blend remaining ingredients well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack and serve with Cool Whip.

title: frozen chocolate bananas
directions: Peel bananas and cut crosswise into halves.
Insert a wooden stick at each end.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put in freezer 2 to 3 hours.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar; gradually add salt, egg yolk and flour, beating smooth after each addition.
Spread batter on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Remove from oven and break Hershey bars into pieces.
Place on top until melted.
Spread and add pecans.
Cool.

title: favorite chess pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, milk, flour, vanilla and margarine until well mixed.
Stir in coconut and pecans and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mint vinegar
directions: Heat vinegar to 150° in saucepan.
Using citrus zester or paring knife, cut strips of rind from lemon, reserving lemon for other uses.
Combine lemon rind, mint leaves and honey; add hot vinegar.
Stir with a wooden spoon, gently bruising leaves; pour into two 1 quart jars.
Cover and store at room temperature 2 weeks.
Pour mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into decorative bottles or jars, discarding mint.
Place a mint sprig in each bottle, if desired.
Store in a cool, dark place up to 6 months. Yields 6 cups.

title: chicken kamouh
directions: Cut chicken cutlets into cubes, about 1/2 to 1-inch.
Roll chicken pieces in flour.
In large pot, saute floured chicken in butter until lightly browned, over low heat.
Add mushrooms and peppers into pan.
Add wine and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until peppers are softened.
This meal can be served over rice or noodles.

title: mary's rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, water, sugar and milk.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Add other ingredients.
Knead well and let rise until double in warm place (about 1 hour).
Punch down and place in refrigerator for future use.
Shape rolls as desired and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package directions minus 1/2 cup water.
Refrigerate.
When Jell-O is almost set, add cranberry-orange relish, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Stir several times before completely set.
Serves about 15.

title: wassail
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon sticks and 3 lemon slices in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes and strain.
Heat, but do not boil the remaining ingredients.
Combine with syrup.
Garnish with lemon slices and serve hot.

title: sunday supper
directions: Brown onion slightly and then add hamburger and brown.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer cabbage, onion and green pepper on bottom.
Then layer of hamburger, then layer of Spanish rice (can), salt and pepper. Pour tomato juice over.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water for 5 minutes.
Stir until blended. Measure sugar, salt and shortening into a mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour to make a thick batter and beat until smooth.
Add yeast and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 cups more flour and work in enough additional flour to make a dough that does not stick to fingers.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and knead for 2 minutes, until dough is springy and elastic.
Shape into a ball and put into a bowl rubbed with shortening.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: In medium saucepan, combine rhubarb, sugar, cornstarch and water; bring to a boil, stirring often. Cook until thick and bubbly, then stir in baking soda and vanilla. Remove from heat. In large bowl, cut butter into oats, flour and brown sugar until crumbly. Pat 3/4 of mixture over bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Spread rhubarb filling over crust. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 dozen. Freezes well.

title: stuffed pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir spinach, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg white, Parmesan cheese, garlic, basil and nutmeg until mixed.
Fill each pasta shell with heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.
Place shells in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.
Nutrition information per serving: 320 calories; 12 grams total fat; 20 mg cholesterol; 430 mg sodium; 22 grams protein and 32 grams carbohydrates.

title: microwave tuna casserole
directions: Saute onions and
celery
in stick of oleo in microwave for 5 minutes.
Combine
noodles,
tuna, soup, milk and onion-celery mixture.
Set
microwave
on Roast for 8 minutes.
Also good with yellow cheese added (Velveeta or Cheddar).

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add the vegetable soup, the mushroom soup and the noodles.
Mix.
Put into oven for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: quick baked beans
directions: In skillet, brown salt pork or cook bacon until about half done.
Lift out with slotted spoon.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and place in bowl of cold water and let sit.
In skillet on low fire, melt margarine and add milk and flour, a little at a time, until smooth.
Then add shredded cheese and season to taste (salt and pepper).

title: apricot salad
directions: In a small saucepan, mix 1 egg (slightly beaten), sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Cook until thickens.
Add 1/2 cup soft cream cheese.
Set aside to cool.
In a separate bowl, mix apricot jello with water.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Add mixture in saucepan to gelatin.
Let congeal.
Add Cool Whip to top.

title: baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together cottage cheese, milk, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Transfer mixture to a shallow dish; place bread in it and let stand for 10 minutes. Turn bread over and let stand another 10 minutes.
Grease a baking sheet and place it in a preheated oven for 7 minutes. Remove baking sheet from oven; place bread on it.
Bake 6 minutes. Turn bread over and bake 5 to 6 minutes more, until golden brown. Serve with maple or jam.
Serves 4.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning (both packages). Add tomato sauce and tomato and green chiles.
Mix together in a bowl the Monterey Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese, beaten eggs and cottage cheese.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan: half meat sauce, 3 tortillas, half cheese mixture and layer again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with chopped lettuce and tomato.

title: minty pie
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.
Combine milk and marshmallow in top of double boiler.
Heat and stir until melted. Cool slightly.
Add syrup and blend.
Fold whipped cream into mixture and pour into crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 6 hours or overnight.
Decorate with chocolate curls or whole fresh strawberries.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese, ground chuck, mushroom soup and tomato bits in a crock-pot.
Add jalapeno peppers and a little juice of peppers if taste requires hotter.
Heat on low for 1 to 2 hours until cheese is melted.
Serves about 30.
Need 2 bags plain nacho chips.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring remaining 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Add gelatin mixture, stirring until dissolved. Cream sugar and cream cheese together in a large bowl; add gelatin mixture, pineapple, grapefruit sections and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into 6 cup oiled mold; chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: soft custard
directions: Scald milk in a saucepan over low heat or in a double boiler. Beat eggs and add to scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Place in top of a double boiler and cook over simmering water until the custard thickens.
Let set in a pan of cold water or by pouring the custard into a chilled bowl.
Stir in vanilla.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Beat egg and soy sauce together.
Dip chicken in egg, then in crumbs, sesame seed and ginger mix.
Saute in nonstick pan sprayed with Pam or bake in oven 20 minutes at 375° or until done. Serves 4.

title: trifle
directions: The vanilla pudding should be done first.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, then fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in crock-pot; add about 2 cups water, margarine and salt.
Cook overnight or about 6 hours on low.
Remove from crock-pot.
Let cool, then remove chicken from bones.
Set aside.

title: dip o'lea
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Warm with all other ingredients in crock-pot and serve with vegetables or chips.

title: double-chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix
in
order	of
ingredients.
Grease
pan and place mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan or 2 round 9-inch pans;	bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, creaming together.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Sift cake mix and jello together in a mixing bowl.
Add 2 eggs and strawberries to dry ingredients.
Beat 10 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise and chill.

title: french rice
directions: Combine
soup
and
butter; stir well.	Drain mushrooms and chestnuts (reserve liquid).
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add mushrooms, chestnuts, liquid and rice to soup mixture;
stir
well.
Pour
into lightly greased baking dish, 10 x 6 x 2-inches.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cha gio
directions: Rinse bean thread in water and soften in hot water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cut thread stack a few times to shorten threads to about 1-inch.
Dice or process onion and carrots to medium grain size (rice, not salt).
Combine bean thread, onion, carrots, egg, seasoning and meat in large something or another.
Mixing with hands works best, but chop sticks work great, too.
Fork?
I dunno. Try it.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add bell pepper, onion and mushrooms. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix. Simmer 15 minutes more.
Boil noodles according to directions on box.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with noodles, meat, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue layering until all mix is used.
Place in 350° oven until hot and bubbling.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate overnight.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine potatoes and oleo in a medium bowl. Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended. Add coconut, salt and vanilla; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand until firm. Yields 24 candies.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add all except margarine.
Pour in a baking dish.
Cut margarine on top.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: old-timey bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into cubes and place in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with raisins.
Mix eggs, 1/4 cup of sugar, salt, milk and water and pour over raisins.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add vanilla and stir.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rosemary's fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken thoroughly in cold water.
Remove skin from chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoning, black pepper and salt. Roll each piece in flour, then put in black skillet containing Crisco oil.

Make sure oil is about 3/4-inch deep in skillet. After placing chicken into hot cooking oil (350° or medium heat), sprinkle again with black pepper and all-purpose seasoning. Brown chicken thoroughly, then turn over and brown thoroughly. Turn heat down just a little and cover skillet with lid.
Cook about 4 minutes more, then remove from skillet and serve.

title: layered deluxe beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef in margarine and add tomato sauce.
Add mushrooms; simmer and set aside to cool.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread half the drained noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and top with cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles.
Spread meat and tomato mixture on top.
Cover with foil and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
(It will be a stiff batter.)
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar or good with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine corn, corn meal, half of the Cheddar cheese, milk, eggs, peppers, salt and baking soda in bowl; mix well. Put butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole or 9-inch iron skillet.

Place in preheated hot oven at 400° until butter is hot but not brown. Immediately pour in batter. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. If after about 35 minutes the top appears too brown, cover with foil.
Serve hot.

title: apple bread
directions: Grate apples and pour oil over and set aside.

title: individual barbecue meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients, except barbecue sauce, together.
Shape into 6 loaves. Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Pour on barbecue sauce and bake 15 minutes longer. You can use purchased barbecue sauce or make your own.

title: chicken delight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a baking dish, spreading the cheese evenly over the top.
Turkey works very well in this recipe as a substitute for chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: Place oats in large bowl and cover with 2 cups boiling water. Let stand for at least 15 minutes (should not be hotter than 90° to 110°). Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Let stand 5 minutes. In the warm oatmeal mixture, add honey, butter (oil), salt, yeast mixture and sunflower seeds. Add egg for rich flavor. Mix well with enough flour to make a dough that can be handled. Turn out on floured surface. Knead a minute or two. Cover and let stand for 10 minutes. Knead dough, adding flour lightly as needed. Don't add too much at a time. Place dough in a greased bowl, coating with a light oil. Cover. Let raise for about 1 hour or until dough doubles in size. Punch down and form into 2 to 3 loaves. Roll in oatmeal to coat. Let raise again and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until done. Cool and enjoy.

title: super easy spaghetti
directions: Boil noodles 8 to 10 minutes.
While cooking, pour spaghetti sauce in casserole.
Cut up sausages into fourths and stir in with sauce.
When noodles are cooked, add to sauce; stir well.
Cover; heat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made right before eating or a day early.
Serve with green salad or cooked green vegies and bread.
Easy and delicious!

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Whip until smooth.

title: old fashioned pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugars, cream and water in a saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered sheet.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef; drain and add seasoning.
Chill.
Add cheese, onion, tomatoes, lettuce and crushed taco chips (save some for garnish).
Mix all together with 8 ounces Green Goddess dressing.

title: chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles for 5 minutes, drain and put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In separate pan, mix cream of chicken soup and milk. (Be sure to keep smooth.)
Add chicken and peas, pour over noodle mixture and mix well.
Crunch potato chips in bag and pour over top of chicken-noodle mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and let sit for 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and place in flat casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, oil, brown sugar and white sugar. Add the vanilla. Blend. Fold in the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add the Rice Krispies, oats, coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Allow space for expanding.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Drain 1 can of raspberries and sprinkle on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of sugar mixed with 1 cup raspberry juice.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Test with a toothpick.

title: chicken-by-cracky
directions: Wash and dry chicken; mix egg and milk with spices in shallow pan.
Crush crackers and dip chicken into egg mixture and roll in crumbs.
Brown chicken in oil on both sides; drain.
Place excess crumbs in casserole dish and add chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: campstove bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and beer.
Stir just until mixed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Cook cake mix as directed and cool.
Mix with mixer, pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Spread over cooled cake.
Then spread pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
You may change the pineapple to any other fruit topping.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in medium saucepan; remove from heat. Stir in sugar and blend eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, stirring in flour and nuts, mix well.
Spread into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 16 squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix in melted oleo, milk and vanilla.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Use frozen pastry shell for crust.

title: in a snappy turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half of batter in cake pan; bake 20 minutes or until set at 350°.
Melt caramels and pour over cooled cake.
Pour chocolate bits on top of melted caramels. Sprinkle pecans on top of chocolate bits.
Pour rest of batter on top and bake another 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place egg in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and beat well with fork.
Stir in milk, sugar, corn, crackers and butter.
Microwave at Medium for 7 minutes and stir well.
Sprinkle with paprika, microwave at Medium for 11 to 14 minutes, rotating after every 5 minutes.
When done, center will barely be set.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Add butter, cheese and eggs to hot spaghetti.
Form mixture into "crust" in 10-inch pie plate. Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Brown ground beef with onion in skillet and drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spread sauce over cottage cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Mix spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato sauce.
Pour over chicken. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover just until cheese melts.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Stir together 1 1/4 cups of flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the butter or margarine, 3/4 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg until blended.
Add flour mixture and milk; beat only until smooth.
Spread over bottom of buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle strawberries on top.

title: sunset punch
directions: Combine the cranberry juice, lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice in a punch bowl. Stir in the ginger ale gently. Scoop the sherbet into the punch. Serve immediately. Yield: 1 1/2 gallons.

title: three-chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rapid boil; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; stir in marshmallows until melted.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add chocolate bars and baking chocolate; stir until melted.
Fold in vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Yields 5 1/2 pounds.

title: orange jello cake
directions: Split cakes lengthwise.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with cakes, cut side up.
Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Stir in ice cream to jello until well mixed.
Add pineapple and soft drink; pour over cakes.
Chill.
Keep chilled.

title: easy turkey dressing
directions: Tear bread into crumbs.
On stove, cook soup, broth, margarine, celery, onion and spices slowly until celery is tender. Pour in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: coconut coffee
directions: Heat together coconut, milk and sugar.
Liquefy in blender and strain.
Add coffee; reheat.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream and a sprinkling of toasted coconut.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in 6-quart pan.
Bring to boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix. Stir in corn flakes, one cup at a time and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes about 40 to 50.

title: mark's favorite turkey dumplings
directions: Cook turkey giblets in water.
Add bouillon cubes.
When giblets are done, remove them from broth and salt and pepper. While broth is boiling hard, open a can of biscuits and tear into pieces; drop in broth.
Cover tight and reduce to low heat.
Keep the cover on to keep the dumplings light and fluffy.

title: cocktail meatballs (with sauce)(these meatballs freeze perfectly!)
directions: Beat egg; add salt, pepper and bread cubes. Add beef and minced onion; mix well.

title: stuffed manicotti with four cheeses
directions: Cook manicotti as package directs; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown and drain sausage. Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Provolone cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg.
Mix well and stuff manicotti.

title: cream sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until very light.
Heat over hot water, beating until foamy.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; stir well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, soda and salt. Beat butter and peanut butter together for 30 seconds.
Add sugars; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in peanuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in additional sugar if desired.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross marking with a fork.
Bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes or until done.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl, reserving 1/2 cup walnuts for frosting.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and cocoa; repeat 4 or 5 times until well blended.
Beat egg whites and salt together; sprinkle with cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff and holds a peak. Gradually fold in sugar, then flour-cocoa mixture.
Use an over-under motion with a spatula.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix together.
Roll out dough thin and use cookie cutters. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Heat remaining ingredients together until hot.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Cool and store, covered, in refrigerator.
Great served on lettuce.

title: bradley's treat
directions: In microwave, melt a few squares of chocolate.
Using tongs dip crackers in chocolate.
Put on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate until hardens.
Store in covered container. Need not refrigerate.

title: fudge dessert
directions: Bake cake according to package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, poke holes in cakes with a wooden spoon handle or a straw.
Pour milk over cake.
Warm fudge sauce and pour over milk. Cool cake completely.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips or crushed Heath bars.

title: mushrooms baked in foil
directions: Rinse, pat dry, trim and place mushrooms in center of sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bring edges of foil up over mushroom mixture and crimp to seal.
Set in baking pan and bake in unpreheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until mushrooms are cooked.
Makes 6 servings, about 24 calories each.

title: play dough
directions: Mix water, oil, and coloring. Mix in flour, salt, and cream of tartar. Cook on stovetop until dough adheres, stirring constantly (about 6-7 minutes). Store in Ziploc bags or an airtight container.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix and roll wieners in mixture.
Fry in deep, hot frying pan until golden brown.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until onion is transparent. Mix remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat grated carrots, egg yolks, lemon juice and oil together thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt, sugar, cinnamon and baking powder and slowly mix this into carrot mixture.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake one hour or until done.
Combine cream cheese, butter, confectioners sugar, raisins and vanilla.
Spread over the cooled cake.
